Structs/TestCallBytes.html#/s:5TDLib13Te.abstract: Returns the received bytes; for testing only. This is an offline method. Can be called before authorization

Structs/AddLogMessage.html#/s:5TDLib13Ad.abstract: Adds a message to TDLib internal log. This is an offline method. Can be called before authorization. Can be called synchronously

Structs/GetLogTags.html#/s:5TDLib10GetLo.name: init()
Structs/GetLogTags.html#/s:5TDLib10GetLo.abstract: Returns list of available TDLib internal log tags, for example, [“actor”, “binlog”, “connections”, “notifications”, “proxy”]. This is an offline method. Can be called before authorization. Can be called synchronously

Structs/GetLogVerbosityLevel.html#/s:5TD.name: init()

Value 0 corresponds to fatal errors, value 1 corresponds to errors, value 2 corresponds to warnings and debug warnings, value 3 corresponds to informational, value 4 corresponds to debug, value 5 corresponds to verbose debug, value greater than 5 and up to 1023 can be used to enable even more logging

Structs/SetLogVerbosityLevel.html#/s:5TD.name: init(newVerbosityLevel:)
Structs/SetLogVerbosityLevel.html#/s:5TD.abstract: Sets the verbosity level of the internal logging of TDLib. This is an offline method. Can be called before authorization. Can be called synchronously

Structs/GetProxies.html#/s:5TDLib10GetPr.abstract: Returns list of proxies that are currently set up. Can be called before authorization

Structs/RemoveProxy.html#/s:5TDLib11Remo.name: init(proxyId:)

Structs/GetCountryCode.html#/s:5TDLib14G.name: init()

Structs/SendPassportAuthorizationForm.ht.abstract: Sends a Telegram Passport authorization form, effectively sharing data with the service. This method must be called after getPassportAuthorizationFormAvailableElements if some previously available elements need to be used

Structs/CheckPhoneNumberVerificationCode.name: init(code:)
Structs/CheckPhoneNumberVerificationCode.abstract: Checks the phone number verification code for Telegram Passport

Structs/ResendPhoneNumberVerificationCod.abstract: Re-sends the code to verify a phone number to be added to a user’s Telegram Passport

Structs/SendPhoneNumberVerificationCode..abstract: The phone number of the user, in international format

Structs/GetPassportElement.html#/s:5TDLi.name: init(type:password:)

Structs/GetAutoDownloadSettingsPresets.h.abstract: Returns auto-download settings presets for the currently logged in user

Structs/ResetNetworkStatistics.html#/s:5.name: init()

Structs/GetNetworkStatistics.html#/s:5TD.name: init(onlyCurrent:)
Structs/GetNetworkStatistics.html#/s:5TD.abstract: Returns network data usage statistics. Can be called before authorization

Structs/SetNetworkType.html#/s:5TDLib14S.name: type

Structs/SetNetworkType.html#/s:5TDLib14S.name: init(type:)
Structs/SetNetworkType.html#/s:5TDLib14S.abstract: Sets the current network type. Can be called before authorization. Calling this method forces all network connections to reopen, mitigating the delay in switching between different networks, so it should be called whenever the network is changed, even if the network type remains the same. -Network type is used to check whether the library can use the network at all and also for collecting detailed network data usage statistics

Structs/OptimizeStorage.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: size

Structs/OptimizeStorage.html#/s:5TDLib15.abstract: Limit on the time that has passed since the last time a file was accessed (or creation time for some filesystems). Pass -1 to use the default limit

Structs/OptimizeStorage.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: count

Structs/OptimizeStorage.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: chatLimit
Structs/OptimizeStorage.html#/s:5TDLib15.abstract: Same as in getStorageStatistics. Affects only returned statistics

Structs/OptimizeStorage.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: init(size:ttl:count:immunityDelay:fileTypes:chatIds:excludeChatIds:chatLimit:)

Structs/GetStorageStatisticsFast.html#/s.name: init()

Structs/GetStorageStatistics.html#/s:5TD.name: init(chatLimit:)

Structs/RemoveChatActionBar.html#/s:5TDL.name: init(chatId:)
Structs/RemoveChatActionBar.html#/s:5TDL.abstract: Removes a chat action bar without any other action

Structs/DeleteAccount.html#/s:5TDLib13De.name: reason

Structs/DeleteAccount.html#/s:5TDLib13De.abstract: Deletes the account of the current user, deleting all information associated with the user from the server. Structs/GetAccountTtl.html#/s:5TDLib13Ge.name: init()
Structs/GetAccountTtl.html#/s:5TDLib13Ge.abstract: Returns the period of inactivity after which the account of the current user will automatically be deleted

Structs/SetAccountTtl.html#/s:5TDLib13Se.name: init(ttl:)
Structs/SetAccountTtl.html#/s:5TDLib13Se.abstract: Changes the period of inactivity after which the account of the current user will automatically be deleted

Structs/GetOption.html#/s:5TDLib9GetOpti.abstract: Returns the value of an option by its name. (Check the list of available options on https://core.telegram.org/tdlib/options.) Can be called before authorization

Structs/GetRecentlyVisitedTMeUrls.html#/.abstract: Google Play referrer to identify the user

Structs/GetRecentlyVisitedTMeUrls.html#/.name: init(referrer:)
Structs/GetRecentlyVisitedTMeUrls.html#/.abstract: Returns t.me URLs recently visited by a newly registered user

Structs/SearchStickers.html#/s:5TDLib14S.name: emoji
Structs/SearchStickers.html#/s:5TDLib14S.abstract: String representation of emoji; must be non-empty

Structs/SearchStickers.html#/s:5TDLib14S.name: limit
Structs/SearchStickers.html#/s:5TDLib14S.abstract: The maximum number of stickers to be returned

Structs/SearchStickers.html#/s:5TDLib14S.name: init(emoji:limit:)
Structs/SearchStickers.html#/s:5TDLib14S.abstract: Searches for stickers from public sticker sets that correspond to a given emoji

Structs/GetStickers.html#/s:5TDLib11GetS.name: emoji
Structs/GetStickers.html#/s:5TDLib11GetS.abstract: String representation of emoji. If empty, returns all known installed stickers

Structs/GetStickers.html#/s:5TDLib11GetS.name: limit
Structs/GetStickers.html#/s:5TDLib11GetS.abstract: The maximum number of stickers to be returned

Structs/GetStickers.html#/s:5TDLib11GetS.name: init(emoji:limit:)
Structs/GetStickers.html#/s:5TDLib11GetS.abstract: Returns stickers from the installed sticker sets that correspond to a given emoji. If the emoji is not empty, favorite and recently used stickers may also be returned

Structs/GetUserProfilePhotos.html#/s:5TD.name: offset
Structs/GetUserProfilePhotos.html#/s:5TD.abstract: The number of photos to skip; must be non-negative

Structs/GetUserProfilePhotos.html#/s:5TD.name: limit
Structs/GetUserProfilePhotos.html#/s:5TD.abstract: The maximum number of photos to be returned; up to 100

Structs/GetUserProfilePhotos.html#/s:5TD.name: init(userId:offset:limit:)
Structs/GetUserProfilePhotos.html#/s:5TD.abstract: Returns the profile photos of a user. The result of this query may be outdated: some photos might have been deleted already

Structs/SharePhoneNumber.html#/s:5TDLib1.name: userId
Structs/SharePhoneNumber.html#/s:5TDLib1.abstract: Identifier of the user with whom to share the phone number. The user must be a mutual contact

Structs/SharePhoneNumber.html#/s:5TDLib1.name: init(userId:)
Structs/SharePhoneNumber.html#/s:5TDLib1.abstract: Shares the phone number of the current user with a mutual contact. Supposed to be called when the user clicks on chatActionBarSharePhoneNumber

Structs/ClearImportedContacts.html#/s:5T.name: init()
Structs/ClearImportedContacts.html#/s:5T.abstract: Clears all imported contacts, contact list remains unchanged

Structs/ChangeImportedContacts.html#/s:5.name: contacts
Structs/ChangeImportedContacts.html#/s:5.abstract: The new list of contacts, contact’s vCard are ignored and are not imported

Structs/ChangeImportedContacts.html#/s:5.name: init(contacts:)
Structs/ChangeImportedContacts.html#/s:5.abstract: Changes imported contacts using the list of current user contacts saved on the device. Imports newly added contacts and, if at least the file database is enabled, deletes recently deleted contacts. -Query result depends on the result of the previous query, so only one query is possible at the same time

Structs/GetImportedContactCount.html#/s:.name: init()
Structs/GetImportedContactCount.html#/s:.abstract: Returns the total number of imported contacts

Structs/SearchContacts.html#/s:5TDLib14S.name: query
Structs/SearchContacts.html#/s:5TDLib14S.abstract: Query to search for; may be empty to return all contacts

Structs/SearchContacts.html#/s:5TDLib14S.name: limit
Structs/SearchContacts.html#/s:5TDLib14S.abstract: The maximum number of users to be returned

Structs/SearchContacts.html#/s:5TDLib14S.name: init(query:limit:)
Structs/SearchContacts.html#/s:5TDLib14S.abstract: Searches for the specified query in the first names, last names and usernames of the known user contacts

Structs/ImportContacts.html#/s:5TDLib14I.name: contacts
Structs/ImportContacts.html#/s:5TDLib14I.abstract: The list of contacts to import or edit; contacts’ vCard are ignored and are not imported

Structs/ImportContacts.html#/s:5TDLib14I.name: init(contacts:)
Structs/ImportContacts.html#/s:5TDLib14I.abstract: Adds new contacts or edits existing contacts by their phone numbers; contacts’ user identifiers are ignored

Structs/AddContact.html#/s:5TDLib10AddCo.name: contact
Structs/AddContact.html#/s:5TDLib10AddCo.abstract: The contact to add or edit; phone number can be empty and needs to be specified only if known, vCard is ignored

Structs/AddContact.html#/s:5TDLib10AddCo.name: sharePhoneNumber
Structs/AddContact.html#/s:5TDLib10AddCo.abstract: True, if the new contact needs to be allowed to see current user’s phone number. A corresponding rule to userPrivacySettingShowPhoneNumber will be added if needed. Use the field UserFullInfo.need_phone_number_privacy_exception to check whether the current user needs to be asked to share their phone number

Structs/AddContact.html#/s:5TDLib10AddCo.name: init(contact:sharePhoneNumber:)
Structs/AddContact.html#/s:5TDLib10AddCo.abstract: Adds a user to the contact list or edits an existing contact by their user identifier

Structs/GetBlockedUsers.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: offset
Structs/GetBlockedUsers.html#/s:5TDLib15.abstract: Number of users to skip in the result; must be non-negative

Structs/GetBlockedUsers.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: limit
Structs/GetBlockedUsers.html#/s:5TDLib15.abstract: The maximum number of users to return; up to 100

Structs/GetBlockedUsers.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: init(offset:limit:)
Structs/GetBlockedUsers.html#/s:5TDLib15.abstract: Returns users that were blocked by the current user

Structs/SendCallRating.html#/s:5TDLib14S.name: comment
Structs/SendCallRating.html#/s:5TDLib14S.abstract: An optional user comment if the rating is less than 5

Structs/SendCallRating.html#/s:5TDLib14S.name: problems
Structs/SendCallRating.html#/s:5TDLib14S.abstract: List of the exact types of problems with the call, specified by the user

Structs/DiscardCall.html#/s:5TDLib11Disc.name: connectionId
Structs/DiscardCall.html#/s:5TDLib11Disc.abstract: Identifier of the connection used during the call

Structs/AcceptCall.html#/s:5TDLib10Accep.name: protocol
Structs/AcceptCall.html#/s:5TDLib10Accep.abstract: Description of the call protocols supported by the client

Structs/CreateCall.html#/s:5TDLib10Creat.name: userId
Structs/CreateCall.html#/s:5TDLib10Creat.abstract: Identifier of the user to be called

Structs/CreateCall.html#/s:5TDLib10Creat.name: protocol
Structs/CreateCall.html#/s:5TDLib10Creat.abstract: Description of the call protocols supported by the client

Structs/JoinChatByInviteLink.html#/s:5TD.name: inviteLink
Structs/JoinChatByInviteLink.html#/s:5TD.abstract: Invite link to import; should begin with “https://t.me/joinchat/”, “https://telegram.me/joinchat/”, or “https://telegram.dog/joinchat/”

Structs/JoinChatByInviteLink.html#/s:5TD.name: init(inviteLink:)
Structs/JoinChatByInviteLink.html#/s:5TD.abstract: Uses an invite link to add the current user to the chat if possible. The new member will not be added until the chat state has been synchronized with the server

Structs/CheckChatInviteLink.html#/s:5TDL.name: inviteLink
Structs/CheckChatInviteLink.html#/s:5TDL.abstract: Invite link to be checked; should begin with “https://t.me/joinchat/”, “https://telegram.me/joinchat/”, or “https://telegram.dog/joinchat/”

Structs/CheckChatInviteLink.html#/s:5TDL.name: init(inviteLink:)
Structs/CheckChatInviteLink.html#/s:5TDL.abstract: Checks the validity of an invite link for a chat and returns information about the corresponding chat

Structs/GenerateChatInviteLink.html#/s:5.name: init(chatId:)
Structs/GenerateChatInviteLink.html#/s:5.abstract: Generates a new invite link for a chat; the previously generated link is revoked. Available for basic groups, supergroups, and channels. Requires administrator privileges and can_invite_users right

Structs/DeleteFile.html#/s:5TDLib10Delet.name: init(fileId:)
Structs/DeleteFile.html#/s:5TDLib10Delet.abstract: Deletes a file from the TDLib file cache

Structs/ReadFilePart.html#/s:5TDLib12Rea.name: fileId
Structs/ReadFilePart.html#/s:5TDLib12Rea.abstract: Identifier of the file. The file must be located in the TDLib file cache

Structs/ReadFilePart.html#/s:5TDLib12Rea.name: offset
Structs/ReadFilePart.html#/s:5TDLib12Rea.abstract: The offset from which to read the file

Structs/ReadFilePart.html#/s:5TDLib12Rea.name: count
Structs/ReadFilePart.html#/s:5TDLib12Rea.abstract: Number of bytes to read. An error will be returned if there are not enough bytes available in the file from the specified position. Pass 0 to read all available data from the specified position

Structs/ReadFilePart.html#/s:5TDLib12Rea.name: init(fileId:offset:count:)
Structs/ReadFilePart.html#/s:5TDLib12Rea.abstract: Reads a part of a file from the TDLib file cache and returns read bytes. This method is intended to be used only if the client has no direct access to TDLib’s file system, because it is usually slower than a direct read from the file

Structs/FinishFileGeneration.html#/s:5TD.name: error
Structs/FinishFileGeneration.html#/s:5TD.abstract: If set, means that file generation has failed and should be terminated

Structs/SetFileGenerationProgress.html#/.name: expectedSize
Structs/SetFileGenerationProgress.html#/.abstract: Expected size of the generated file, in bytes; 0 if unknown

Structs/SetFileGenerationProgress.html#/.name: init(generationId:expectedSize:localPrefixSize:)
Structs/SetFileGenerationProgress.html#/.abstract: Informs TDLib on a file generation progress

Structs/WriteGeneratedFilePart.html#/s:5.name: offset
Structs/WriteGeneratedFilePart.html#/s:5.abstract: The offset from which to write the data to the file

Structs/WriteGeneratedFilePart.html#/s:5.name: init(generationId:offset:data:)
Structs/WriteGeneratedFilePart.html#/s:5.abstract: Writes a part of a generated file. This method is intended to be used only if the client has no direct access to TDLib’s file system, because it is usually slower than a direct write to the destination file

Structs/CancelUploadFile.html#/s:5TDLib1.name: fileId
Structs/CancelUploadFile.html#/s:5TDLib1.abstract: Identifier of the file to stop uploading

Structs/CancelUploadFile.html#/s:5TDLib1.name: init(fileId:)
Structs/CancelUploadFile.html#/s:5TDLib1.abstract: Stops the uploading of a file. Supported only for files uploaded by using uploadFile. For other files the behavior is undefined

Structs/UploadFile.html#/s:5TDLib10Uploa.name: priority
Structs/UploadFile.html#/s:5TDLib10Uploa.abstract: Priority of the upload (1-32). The higher the priority, the earlier the file will be uploaded. If the priorities of two files are equal, then the first one for which uploadFile was called will be uploaded first

Structs/UploadFile.html#/s:5TDLib10Uploa.name: init(file:fileType:priority:)
Structs/UploadFile.html#/s:5TDLib10Uploa.abstract: Asynchronously uploads a file to the cloud without sending it in a message. updateFile will be used to notify about upload progress and successful completion of the upload. The file will not have a persistent remote identifier until it will be sent in a message

Structs/CancelDownloadFile.html#/s:5TDLi.name: fileId
Structs/CancelDownloadFile.html#/s:5TDLi.abstract: Identifier of a file to stop downloading

Structs/CancelDownloadFile.html#/s:5TDLi.name: onlyIfPending
Structs/CancelDownloadFile.html#/s:5TDLi.abstract: Pass true to stop downloading only if it hasn’t been started, i.e. request hasn’t been sent to server

Structs/CancelDownloadFile.html#/s:5TDLi.name: init(fileId:onlyIfPending:)
Structs/CancelDownloadFile.html#/s:5TDLi.abstract: Stops the downloading of a file. If a file has already been downloaded, does nothing

Structs/GetFileDownloadedPrefixSize.html.name: offset
Structs/GetFileDownloadedPrefixSize.html.abstract: Offset from which downloaded prefix size should be calculated

Structs/GetFileDownloadedPrefixSize.html.name: init(fileId:offset:)
Structs/GetFileDownloadedPrefixSize.html.abstract: Returns file downloaded prefix size from a given offset

Structs/DownloadFile.html#/s:5TDLib12Dow.name: priority
Structs/DownloadFile.html#/s:5TDLib12Dow.abstract: Priority of the download (1-32). The higher the priority, the earlier the file will be downloaded. If the priorities of two files are equal, then the last one for which downloadFile was called will be downloaded first

Structs/DownloadFile.html#/s:5TDLib12Dow.name: offset
Structs/DownloadFile.html#/s:5TDLib12Dow.abstract: The starting position from which the file should be downloaded

Structs/DownloadFile.html#/s:5TDLib12Dow.name: limit
Structs/DownloadFile.html#/s:5TDLib12Dow.abstract: Number of bytes which should be downloaded starting from the “offset” position before the download will be automatically cancelled; use 0 to download without a limit

Structs/DownloadFile.html#/s:5TDLib12Dow.name: synchronous
Structs/DownloadFile.html#/s:5TDLib12Dow.abstract: If false, this request returns file state just after the download has been started. If true, this request returns file state only after -the download has succeeded, has failed, has been cancelled or a new downloadFile request with different offset/limit parameters was sent

Structs/DownloadFile.html#/s:5TDLib12Dow.name: init(fileId:priority:offset:limit:synchronous:)
Structs/DownloadFile.html#/s:5TDLib12Dow.abstract: Downloads a file from the cloud. Download progress and completion of the download will be notified through updateFile updates

Structs/SetPinnedChats.html#/s:5TDLib14S.name: chatList
Structs/SetPinnedChats.html#/s:5TDLib14S.abstract: Chat list in which to change the order of pinned chats

Structs/ResetAllNotificationSettings.htm.name: init()
Structs/ResetAllNotificationSettings.htm.abstract: Resets all notification settings to their default values. By default, all chats are unmuted, the sound is set to “default” and message previews are shown

Structs/SetScopeNotificationSettings.htm.name: scope
Structs/SetScopeNotificationSettings.htm.abstract: Types of chats for which to change the notification settings

Structs/SetScopeNotificationSettings.htm.name: notificationSettings
Structs/SetScopeNotificationSettings.htm.abstract: The new notification settings for the given scope

Structs/SetScopeNotificationSettings.htm.name: init(scope:notificationSettings:)
Structs/SetScopeNotificationSettings.htm.abstract: Changes notification settings for chats of a given type

Structs/GetScopeNotificationSettings.htm.name: scope
Structs/GetScopeNotificationSettings.htm.abstract: Types of chats for which to return the notification settings information

Structs/GetScopeNotificationSettings.htm.name: init(scope:)
Structs/GetScopeNotificationSettings.htm.abstract: Returns the notification settings for chats of a given type

Structs/GetChatNotificationSettingsExcep.name: scope
Structs/GetChatNotificationSettingsExcep.abstract: If specified, only chats from the specified scope will be returned

Structs/GetChatNotificationSettingsExcep.name: compareSound
Structs/GetChatNotificationSettingsExcep.abstract: If true, also chats with non-default sound will be returned

Structs/GetChatNotificationSettingsExcep.name: init(scope:compareSound:)
Structs/GetChatNotificationSettingsExcep.abstract: Returns list of chats with non-default notification settings

Structs/ClearAllDraftMessages.html#/s:5T.name: excludeSecretChats
Structs/ClearAllDraftMessages.html#/s:5T.abstract: If true, local draft messages in secret chats will not be cleared

Structs/GetChatAdministrators.html#/s:5T.name: init(chatId:)
Structs/GetChatAdministrators.html#/s:5T.abstract: Returns a list of administrators of the chat with their custom titles

Structs/SearchChatMembers.html#/s:5TDLib.name: limit
Structs/SearchChatMembers.html#/s:5TDLib.abstract: The maximum number of users to be returned

Structs/SearchChatMembers.html#/s:5TDLib.name: filter
Structs/SearchChatMembers.html#/s:5TDLib.abstract: The type of users to return. By default, chatMembersFilterMembers

Structs/SearchChatMembers.html#/s:5TDLib.name: init(chatId:query:limit:filter:)
Structs/SearchChatMembers.html#/s:5TDLib.abstract: Searches for a specified query in the first name, last name and username of the members of a specified chat. Requires administrator rights in channels

Structs/GetChatMember.html#/s:5TDLib13Ge.name: init(chatId:userId:)
Structs/GetChatMember.html#/s:5TDLib13Ge.abstract: Returns information about a single member of a chat

Structs/TransferChatOwnership.html#/s:5T.name: userId
Structs/TransferChatOwnership.html#/s:5T.abstract: Identifier of the user to which transfer the ownership. The ownership can’t be transferred to a bot or to a deleted user

Structs/TransferChatOwnership.html#/s:5T.name: init(chatId:userId:password:)
Structs/TransferChatOwnership.html#/s:5T.abstract: Changes the owner of a chat. The current user must be a current owner of the chat. Use the method canTransferOwnership to check whether the ownership can be transferred from the current session. Available only for supergroups and channel chats

Structs/CanTransferOwnership.html#/s:5TD.name: init()
Structs/CanTransferOwnership.html#/s:5TD.abstract: Checks whether the current session can be used to transfer a chat ownership to another user

Structs/SetChatMemberStatus.html#/s:5TDL.name: status
Structs/SetChatMemberStatus.html#/s:5TDL.abstract: The new status of the member in the chat

Structs/SetChatMemberStatus.html#/s:5TDL.name: init(chatId:userId:status:)
Structs/SetChatMemberStatus.html#/s:5TDL.abstract: Changes the status of a chat member, needs appropriate privileges. This function is currently not suitable for adding new members to the chat and transferring chat ownership; instead, use addChatMember or transferChatOwnership. The chat member status will not be changed until it has been synchronized with the server

Structs/AddChatMembers.html#/s:5TDLib14A.name: userIds
Structs/AddChatMembers.html#/s:5TDLib14A.abstract: Identifiers of the users to be added to the chat

Structs/AddChatMembers.html#/s:5TDLib14A.name: init(chatId:userIds:)
Structs/AddChatMembers.html#/s:5TDLib14A.abstract: Adds multiple new members to a chat. Currently this option is only available for supergroups and channels. This option can’t be used to join a chat. Members can’t be added to a channel if it has more than 200 members. Members will not be added until the chat state has been synchronized with the server

Structs/AddChatMember.html#/s:5TDLib13Ad.name: forwardLimit
Structs/AddChatMember.html#/s:5TDLib13Ad.abstract: The number of earlier messages from the chat to be forwarded to the new member; up to 100. Ignored for supergroups and channels

Structs/AddChatMember.html#/s:5TDLib13Ad.name: init(chatId:userId:forwardLimit:)
Structs/AddChatMember.html#/s:5TDLib13Ad.abstract: Adds a new member to a chat. Members can’t be added to private or secret chats. Members will not be added until the chat state has been synchronized with the server

Structs/LeaveChat.html#/s:5TDLib9LeaveCh.name: init(chatId:)
Structs/LeaveChat.html#/s:5TDLib9LeaveCh.abstract: Removes current user from chat members. Private and secret chats can’t be left using this method

Structs/JoinChat.html#/s:5TDLib8JoinChat.name: init(chatId:)
Structs/JoinChat.html#/s:5TDLib8JoinChat.abstract: Adds current user as a new member to a chat. Private and secret chats can’t be joined using this method

Structs/UnpinChatMessage.html#/s:5TDLib1.name: init(chatId:)
Structs/UnpinChatMessage.html#/s:5TDLib1.abstract: Removes the pinned message from a chat; requires can_pin_messages rights in the group or channel

Structs/PinChatMessage.html#/s:5TDLib14P.name: disableNotification
Structs/PinChatMessage.html#/s:5TDLib14P.abstract: True, if there should be no notification about the pinned message

Structs/PinChatMessage.html#/s:5TDLib14P.name: init(chatId:messageId:disableNotification:)
Structs/PinChatMessage.html#/s:5TDLib14P.abstract: Pins a message in a chat; requires can_pin_messages rights

Structs/SetChatSlowModeDelay.html#/s:5TD.name: slowModeDelay
Structs/SetChatSlowModeDelay.html#/s:5TD.abstract: New slow mode delay for the chat; must be one of 0, 10, 30, 60, 300, 900, 3600

Structs/SetChatSlowModeDelay.html#/s:5TD.name: init(chatId:slowModeDelay:)
Structs/SetChatSlowModeDelay.html#/s:5TD.abstract: Changes the slow mode delay of a chat. Available only for supergroups; requires can_restrict_members rights

Structs/SetChatLocation.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: location
Structs/SetChatLocation.html#/s:5TDLib15.abstract: New location for the chat; must be valid and not null

Structs/SetChatLocation.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: init(chatId:location:)
Structs/SetChatLocation.html#/s:5TDLib15.abstract: Changes the location of a chat. Available only for some location-based supergroups, use supergroupFullInfo.can_set_location to check whether the method is allowed to use

Structs/SetChatDiscussionGroup.html#/s:5.name: chatId
Structs/SetChatDiscussionGroup.html#/s:5.abstract: Identifier of the channel chat. Pass 0 to remove a link from the supergroup passed in the second argument to a linked channel chat (requires can_pin_messages rights in the supergroup)

Structs/SetChatDiscussionGroup.html#/s:5.name: discussionChatId
Structs/SetChatDiscussionGroup.html#/s:5.abstract: Identifier of a new channel’s discussion group. Use 0 to remove the discussion group. -Use the method getSuitableDiscussionChats to find all suitable groups. Basic group chats needs to be first upgraded to supergroup chats. If new chat members don’t have access to old messages in the supergroup, then toggleSupergroupIsAllHistoryAvailable needs to be used first to change that

Structs/SetChatDiscussionGroup.html#/s:5.name: init(chatId:discussionChatId:)
Structs/SetChatDiscussionGroup.html#/s:5.abstract: Changes the discussion group of a channel chat; requires can_change_info rights in the channel if it is specified

Structs/SetChatDescription.html#/s:5TDLi.name: init(chatId:description:)
Structs/SetChatDescription.html#/s:5TDLi.abstract: Changes information about a chat. Available for basic groups, supergroups, and channels. Requires can_change_info rights

Structs/SetChatClientData.html#/s:5TDLib.name: init(chatId:clientData:)
Structs/SetChatClientData.html#/s:5TDLib.abstract: Changes client data associated with a chat

Structs/ToggleChatDefaultDisableNotifica.name: init(chatId:defaultDisableNotification:)
Structs/ToggleChatDefaultDisableNotifica.abstract: Changes the value of the default disable_notification parameter, used when a message is sent to a chat

Structs/ToggleChatIsMarkedAsUnread.html#.name: init(chatId:isMarkedAsUnread:)
Structs/ToggleChatIsMarkedAsUnread.html#.abstract: Changes the marked as unread state of a chat

Structs/ToggleChatIsPinned.html#/s:5TDLi.name: init(chatId:isPinned:)
Structs/ToggleChatIsPinned.html#/s:5TDLi.abstract: Changes the pinned state of a chat. You can pin up to GetOption(“pinned_chat_count_max”)/GetOption(“pinned_archived_chat_count_max”) non-secret chats and the same number of secret chats in the main/archive chat list

Structs/SetChatNotificationSettings.html.name: notificationSettings
Structs/SetChatNotificationSettings.html.abstract: New notification settings for the chat. If the chat is muted for more than 1 week, it is considered to be muted forever

Structs/SetChatNotificationSettings.html.name: init(chatId:notificationSettings:)
Structs/SetChatNotificationSettings.html.abstract: Changes the notification settings of a chat. Notification settings of a chat with the current user (Saved Messages) can’t be changed

Structs/SetChatDraftMessage.html#/s:5TDL.name: init(chatId:draftMessage:)
Structs/SetChatDraftMessage.html#/s:5TDL.abstract: Changes the draft message in a chat

Structs/SetChatPermissions.html#/s:5TDLi.name: permissions
Structs/SetChatPermissions.html#/s:5TDLi.abstract: New non-administrator members permissions in the chat

Structs/SetChatPermissions.html#/s:5TDLi.name: init(chatId:permissions:)
Structs/SetChatPermissions.html#/s:5TDLi.abstract: Changes the chat members permissions. Supported only for basic groups and supergroups. Requires can_restrict_members administrator right

Structs/SetChatPhoto.html#/s:5TDLib12Set.name: photo
Structs/SetChatPhoto.html#/s:5TDLib12Set.abstract: New chat photo. You can use a zero InputFileId to delete the chat photo. Files that are accessible only by HTTP URL are not acceptable

Structs/SetChatPhoto.html#/s:5TDLib12Set.name: init(chatId:photo:)
Structs/SetChatPhoto.html#/s:5TDLib12Set.abstract: Changes the photo of a chat. Supported only for basic groups, supergroups and channels. Requires can_change_info rights. The photo will not be changed before request to the server has been completed

Structs/SetChatTitle.html#/s:5TDLib12Set.name: init(chatId:title:)
Structs/SetChatTitle.html#/s:5TDLib12Set.abstract: Changes the chat title. Supported only for basic groups, supergroups and channels. Requires can_change_info rights. The title will not be changed until the request to the server has been completed

Structs/SetChatChatList.html#/s:5TDLib07.name: init(chatId:chatList:)
Structs/SetChatChatList.html#/s:5TDLib07.abstract: Moves a chat to a different chat list. Current chat list of the chat must ne non-null

Structs/UpgradeBasicGroupChatToSupergrou.name: init(chatId:)
Structs/UpgradeBasicGroupChatToSupergrou.abstract: Creates a new supergroup from an existing basic group and sends a corresponding messageChatUpgradeTo and messageChatUpgradeFrom; requires creator privileges. Deactivates the original basic group

Structs/CreateNewSecretChat.html#/s:5TDL.name: init(userId:)
Structs/CreateNewSecretChat.html#/s:5TDL.abstract: Creates a new secret chat. Returns the newly created chat

Structs/CreateNewSupergroupChat.html#/s:.name: isChannel
Structs/CreateNewSupergroupChat.html#/s:.abstract: True, if a channel chat should be created

Structs/CreateNewSupergroupChat.html#/s:.name: location
Structs/CreateNewSupergroupChat.html#/s:.abstract: Chat location if a location-based supergroup is being created

Structs/CreateNewSupergroupChat.html#/s:.name: init(title:isChannel:description:location:)
Structs/CreateNewSupergroupChat.html#/s:.abstract: Creates a new supergroup or channel and sends a corresponding messageSupergroupChatCreate. Returns the newly created chat

Structs/CreateNewBasicGroupChat.html#/s:.name: userIds
Structs/CreateNewBasicGroupChat.html#/s:.abstract: Identifiers of users to be added to the basic group

Structs/CreateNewBasicGroupChat.html#/s:.name: title
Structs/CreateNewBasicGroupChat.html#/s:.abstract: Title of the new basic group; 1-128 characters

Structs/CreateNewBasicGroupChat.html#/s:.name: init(userIds:title:)

Structs/CreateSecretChat.html#/s:5TDLib1.name: init(secretChatId:)

Structs/CreateSupergroupChat.html#/s:5TD.name: force
Structs/CreateSupergroupChat.html#/s:5TD.abstract: If true, the chat will be created without network request. In this case all information about the chat except its type, title and photo can be incorrect

Structs/CreateSupergroupChat.html#/s:5TD.name: init(supergroupId:force:)
Structs/CreateSupergroupChat.html#/s:5TD.abstract: Returns an existing chat corresponding to a known supergroup or channel

Structs/CreateBasicGroupChat.html#/s:5TD.name: force
Structs/CreateBasicGroupChat.html#/s:5TD.abstract: If true, the chat will be created without network request. In this case all information about the chat except its type, title and photo can be incorrect

Structs/CreateBasicGroupChat.html#/s:5TD.name: init(basicGroupId:force:)
Structs/CreateBasicGroupChat.html#/s:5TD.abstract: Returns an existing chat corresponding to a known basic group

Structs/CreatePrivateChat.html#/s:5TDLib.name: force
Structs/CreatePrivateChat.html#/s:5TDLib.abstract: If true, the chat will be created without network request. In this case all information about the chat except its type, title and photo can be incorrect

Structs/CreatePrivateChat.html#/s:5TDLib.name: init(userId:force:)
Structs/CreatePrivateChat.html#/s:5TDLib.abstract: Returns an existing chat corresponding to a given user

Structs/ReadAllChatMentions.html#/s:5TDL.name: init(chatId:)
Structs/ReadAllChatMentions.html#/s:5TDL.abstract: Marks all mentions in a chat as read

Structs/OpenMessageContent.html#/s:5TDLi.name: messageId
Structs/OpenMessageContent.html#/s:5TDLi.abstract: Identifier of the message with the opened content

Structs/OpenMessageContent.html#/s:5TDLi.name: init(chatId:messageId:)
Structs/OpenMessageContent.html#/s:5TDLi.abstract: Informs TDLib that the message content has been opened (e.g., the user has opened a photo, video, document, location or venue, or has listened to an audio file or voice note message). An updateMessageContentOpened update will be generated if something has changed

Structs/ViewMessages.html#/s:5TDLib12Vie.name: messageIds
Structs/ViewMessages.html#/s:5TDLib12Vie.abstract: The identifiers of the messages being viewed

Structs/ViewMessages.html#/s:5TDLib12Vie.name: forceRead
Structs/ViewMessages.html#/s:5TDLib12Vie.abstract: True, if messages in closed chats should be marked as read

Structs/ViewMessages.html#/s:5TDLib12Vie.name: init(chatId:messageIds:forceRead:)
Structs/ViewMessages.html#/s:5TDLib12Vie.abstract: Informs TDLib that messages are being viewed by the user. Many useful activities depend on whether the messages are currently being viewed or not (e.g., marking messages as read, incrementing a view counter, updating a view counter, removing deleted messages in supergroups and channels)

Structs/CloseChat.html#/s:5TDLib9CloseCh.name: init(chatId:)
Structs/CloseChat.html#/s:5TDLib9CloseCh.abstract: Informs TDLib that the chat is closed by the user. Many useful activities depend on the chat being opened or closed

Structs/OpenChat.html#/s:5TDLib8OpenChat.name: init(chatId:)
Structs/OpenChat.html#/s:5TDLib8OpenChat.abstract: Informs TDLib that the chat is opened by the user. Many useful activities depend on the chat being opened or closed (e.g., in supergroups and channels all updates are received only for opened chats)

Structs/SendChatAction.html#/s:5TDLib14S.name: init(chatId:action:)
Structs/SendChatAction.html#/s:5TDLib14S.abstract: Sends a notification about user activity in a chat

Structs/DeleteChatReplyMarkup.html#/s:5T.name: messageId
Structs/DeleteChatReplyMarkup.html#/s:5T.abstract: The message identifier of the used keyboard

Structs/DeleteChatReplyMarkup.html#/s:5T.name: init(chatId:messageId:)
Structs/DeleteChatReplyMarkup.html#/s:5T.abstract: Deletes the default reply markup from a chat. Must be called after a one-time keyboard or a ForceReply reply markup has been used. UpdateChatReplyMarkup will be sent if the reply markup will be changed

Structs/GetInlineGameHighScores.html#/s:.name: init(inlineMessageId:userId:)
Structs/GetInlineGameHighScores.html#/s:.abstract: Returns game high scores and some part of the high score table in the range of the specified user; for bots only

Structs/GetGameHighScores.html#/s:5TDLib.name: chatId
Structs/GetGameHighScores.html#/s:5TDLib.abstract: The chat that contains the message with the game

Structs/GetGameHighScores.html#/s:5TDLib.name: init(chatId:messageId:userId:)
Structs/GetGameHighScores.html#/s:5TDLib.abstract: Returns the high scores for a game and some part of the high score table in the range of the specified user; for bots only

Structs/SetInlineGameScore.html#/s:5TDLi.name: editMessage
Structs/SetInlineGameScore.html#/s:5TDLi.abstract: True, if the message should be edited

Structs/SetInlineGameScore.html#/s:5TDLi.name: force
Structs/SetInlineGameScore.html#/s:5TDLi.abstract: Pass true to update the score even if it decreases. If the score is 0, the user will be deleted from the high score table

Structs/SetInlineGameScore.html#/s:5TDLi.name: init(inlineMessageId:editMessage:userId:score:force:)
Structs/SetInlineGameScore.html#/s:5TDLi.abstract: Updates the game score of the specified user in a game; for bots only

Structs/SetGameScore.html#/s:5TDLib12Set.name: chatId
Structs/SetGameScore.html#/s:5TDLib12Set.abstract: The chat to which the message with the game belongs

Structs/SetGameScore.html#/s:5TDLib12Set.name: editMessage
Structs/SetGameScore.html#/s:5TDLib12Set.abstract: True, if the message should be edited

Structs/SetGameScore.html#/s:5TDLib12Set.name: force
Structs/SetGameScore.html#/s:5TDLib12Set.abstract: Pass true to update the score even if it decreases. If the score is 0, the user will be deleted from the high score table

Structs/SetGameScore.html#/s:5TDLib12Set.name: init(chatId:messageId:editMessage:userId:score:force:)
Structs/SetGameScore.html#/s:5TDLib12Set.abstract: Updates the game score of the specified user in the game; for bots only

Structs/AnswerPreCheckoutQuery.html#/s:5.name: init(preCheckoutQueryId:errorMessage:)
Structs/AnswerPreCheckoutQuery.html#/s:5.abstract: Sets the result of a pre-checkout query; for bots only

Structs/AnswerShippingQuery.html#/s:5TDL.name: init(shippingQueryId:shippingOptions:errorMessage:)
Structs/AnswerShippingQuery.html#/s:5TDL.abstract: Sets the result of a shipping query; for bots only

Structs/AnswerCallbackQuery.html#/s:5TDL.name: showAlert
Structs/AnswerCallbackQuery.html#/s:5TDL.abstract: If true, an alert should be shown to the user instead of a toast notification

Structs/AnswerCallbackQuery.html#/s:5TDL.name: cacheTime
Structs/AnswerCallbackQuery.html#/s:5TDL.abstract: Time during which the result of the query can be cached, in seconds

Structs/AnswerCallbackQuery.html#/s:5TDL.name: init(callbackQueryId:text:showAlert:url:cacheTime:)
Structs/AnswerCallbackQuery.html#/s:5TDL.abstract: Sets the result of a callback query; for bots only

Structs/GetCallbackQueryAnswer.html#/s:5.name: chatId
Structs/GetCallbackQueryAnswer.html#/s:5.abstract: Identifier of the chat with the message

Structs/GetCallbackQueryAnswer.html#/s:5.name: messageId
Structs/GetCallbackQueryAnswer.html#/s:5.abstract: Identifier of the message from which the query originated

Structs/GetCallbackQueryAnswer.html#/s:5.name: init(chatId:messageId:payload:)
Structs/GetCallbackQueryAnswer.html#/s:5.abstract: Sends a callback query to a bot and returns an answer. Returns an error with code 502 if the bot fails to answer the query before the query timeout expires

Structs/AnswerInlineQuery.html#/s:5TDLib.name: isPersonal
Structs/AnswerInlineQuery.html#/s:5TDLib.abstract: True, if the result of the query can be cached for the specified user

Structs/AnswerInlineQuery.html#/s:5TDLib.name: cacheTime
Structs/AnswerInlineQuery.html#/s:5TDLib.abstract: Allowed time to cache the results of the query, in seconds

Structs/AnswerInlineQuery.html#/s:5TDLib.name: nextOffset
Structs/AnswerInlineQuery.html#/s:5TDLib.abstract: Offset for the next inline query; pass an empty string if there are no more results

Structs/AnswerInlineQuery.html#/s:5TDLib.name: switchPmText
Structs/AnswerInlineQuery.html#/s:5TDLib.abstract: If non-empty, this text should be shown on the button that opens a private chat with the bot and sends a start message to the bot with the parameter switch_pm_parameter

Structs/AnswerInlineQuery.html#/s:5TDLib.name: switchPmParameter
Structs/AnswerInlineQuery.html#/s:5TDLib.abstract: The parameter for the bot start message

Structs/AnswerInlineQuery.html#/s:5TDLib.name: init(inlineQueryId:isPersonal:results:cacheTime:nextOffset:switchPmText:switchPmParameter:)
Structs/AnswerInlineQuery.html#/s:5TDLib.abstract: Sets the result of an inline query; for bots only

Structs/GetInlineQueryResults.html#/s:5T.name: chatId
Structs/GetInlineQueryResults.html#/s:5T.abstract: Identifier of the chat where the query was sent

Structs/GetInlineQueryResults.html#/s:5T.name: userLocation
Structs/GetInlineQueryResults.html#/s:5T.abstract: Location of the user, only if needed

Structs/GetInlineQueryResults.html#/s:5T.name: offset
Structs/GetInlineQueryResults.html#/s:5T.abstract: Offset of the first entry to return

Structs/GetInlineQueryResults.html#/s:5T.name: init(botUserId:chatId:userLocation:query:offset:)
Structs/GetInlineQueryResults.html#/s:5T.abstract: Sends an inline query to a bot and returns its results. Returns an error with code 502 if the bot fails to answer the query before the query timeout expires

Structs/GetLoginUrl.html#/s:5TDLib11GetL.name: chatId
Structs/GetLoginUrl.html#/s:5TDLib11GetL.abstract: Chat identifier of the message with the button

Structs/GetLoginUrl.html#/s:5TDLib11GetL.name: messageId
Structs/GetLoginUrl.html#/s:5TDLib11GetL.abstract: Message identifier of the message with the button

Structs/GetLoginUrl.html#/s:5TDLib11GetL.name: allowWriteAccess
Structs/GetLoginUrl.html#/s:5TDLib11GetL.abstract: True, if the user allowed the bot to send them messages

Structs/GetLoginUrl.html#/s:5TDLib11GetL.name: init(chatId:messageId:buttonId:allowWriteAccess:)
Structs/GetLoginUrl.html#/s:5TDLib11GetL.abstract: Returns an HTTP URL which can be used to automatically authorize the user on a website after clicking an inline button of type inlineKeyboardButtonTypeLoginUrl. -Use the method getLoginUrlInfo to find whether a prior user confirmation is needed. If an error is returned, then the button must be handled as an ordinary URL button

Structs/GetLoginUrlInfo.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: chatId
Structs/GetLoginUrlInfo.html#/s:5TDLib15.abstract: Chat identifier of the message with the button

Structs/GetLoginUrlInfo.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: messageId
Structs/GetLoginUrlInfo.html#/s:5TDLib15.abstract: Message identifier of the message with the button

Structs/GetLoginUrlInfo.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: init(chatId:messageId:buttonId:)
Structs/GetLoginUrlInfo.html#/s:5TDLib15.abstract: Returns information about a button of type inlineKeyboardButtonTypeLoginUrl. The method needs to be called when the user presses the button

Structs/StopPoll.html#/s:5TDLib8StopPoll.name: chatId
Structs/StopPoll.html#/s:5TDLib8StopPoll.abstract: Identifier of the chat to which the poll belongs

Structs/StopPoll.html#/s:5TDLib8StopPoll.name: messageId
Structs/StopPoll.html#/s:5TDLib8StopPoll.abstract: Identifier of the message containing the poll

Structs/StopPoll.html#/s:5TDLib8StopPoll.name: replyMarkup
Structs/StopPoll.html#/s:5TDLib8StopPoll.abstract: The new message reply markup; for bots only

Structs/StopPoll.html#/s:5TDLib8StopPoll.name: init(chatId:messageId:replyMarkup:)
Structs/StopPoll.html#/s:5TDLib8StopPoll.abstract: Stops a poll. A poll in a message can be stopped when the message has can_be_edited flag set

Structs/GetPollVoters.html#/s:5TDLib13Ge.name: chatId
Structs/GetPollVoters.html#/s:5TDLib13Ge.abstract: Identifier of the chat to which the poll belongs

Structs/GetPollVoters.html#/s:5TDLib13Ge.name: messageId
Structs/GetPollVoters.html#/s:5TDLib13Ge.abstract: Identifier of the message containing the poll

Structs/GetPollVoters.html#/s:5TDLib13Ge.name: offset
Structs/GetPollVoters.html#/s:5TDLib13Ge.abstract: Number of users to skip in the result; must be non-negative

Structs/GetPollVoters.html#/s:5TDLib13Ge.name: limit
Structs/GetPollVoters.html#/s:5TDLib13Ge.abstract: The maximum number of users to be returned; must be positive and can’t be greater than 50. Fewer users may be returned than specified by the limit, even if the end of the voter list has not been reached

Structs/GetPollVoters.html#/s:5TDLib13Ge.name: init(chatId:messageId:optionId:offset:limit:)
Structs/GetPollVoters.html#/s:5TDLib13Ge.abstract: Returns users voted for the specified option in a non-anonymous polls. For the optimal performance the number of returned users is chosen by the library

Structs/SetPollAnswer.html#/s:5TDLib13Se.name: chatId
Structs/SetPollAnswer.html#/s:5TDLib13Se.abstract: Identifier of the chat to which the poll belongs

Structs/SetPollAnswer.html#/s:5TDLib13Se.name: messageId
Structs/SetPollAnswer.html#/s:5TDLib13Se.abstract: Identifier of the message containing the poll

Structs/SetPollAnswer.html#/s:5TDLib13Se.name: optionIds
Structs/SetPollAnswer.html#/s:5TDLib13Se.abstract: 0-based identifiers of answer options, chosen by the user. User can choose more than 1 answer option only is the poll allows multiple answers

Structs/SetPollAnswer.html#/s:5TDLib13Se.name: init(chatId:messageId:optionIds:)
Structs/SetPollAnswer.html#/s:5TDLib13Se.abstract: Changes the user answer to a poll. A poll in quiz mode can be answered only once

Structs/GetJsonString.html#/s:5TDLib13Ge.name: init(jsonValue:)
Structs/GetJsonString.html#/s:5TDLib13Ge.abstract: Converts a JsonValue object to corresponding JSON-serialized string. This is an offline method. Can be called before authorization. Can be called synchronously

Structs/GetJsonValue.html#/s:5TDLib12Get.name: init(json:)
Structs/GetJsonValue.html#/s:5TDLib12Get.abstract: Converts a JSON-serialized string to corresponding JsonValue object. This is an offline method. Can be called before authorization. Can be called synchronously

Structs/GetLanguagePackString.html#/s:5T.name: languagePackDatabasePath
Structs/GetLanguagePackString.html#/s:5T.abstract: Path to the language pack database in which strings are stored

Structs/GetLanguagePackString.html#/s:5T.name: localizationTarget
Structs/GetLanguagePackString.html#/s:5T.abstract: Localization target to which the language pack belongs

Structs/GetLanguagePackString.html#/s:5T.name: key
Structs/GetLanguagePackString.html#/s:5T.abstract: Language pack key of the string to be returned

Structs/GetLanguagePackString.html#/s:5T.name: init(languagePackDatabasePath:localizationTarget:languagePackId:key:)
Structs/GetLanguagePackString.html#/s:5T.abstract: Returns a string stored in the local database from the specified localization target and language pack by its key. Returns a 404 error if the string is not found. This is an offline method. Can be called before authorization. Can be called synchronously

Structs/CleanFileName.html#/s:5TDLib13Cl.name: fileName
Structs/CleanFileName.html#/s:5TDLib13Cl.abstract: File name or path to the file

Structs/CleanFileName.html#/s:5TDLib13Cl.name: init(fileName:)
Structs/CleanFileName.html#/s:5TDLib13Cl.abstract: Removes potentially dangerous characters from the name of a file. The encoding of the file name is supposed to be UTF-8. Returns an empty string on failure. This is an offline method. Can be called before authorization. Can be called synchronously

Structs/GetFileExtension.html#/s:5TDLib1.name: init(mimeType:)
Structs/GetFileExtension.html#/s:5TDLib1.abstract: Returns the extension of a file, guessed by its MIME type. Returns an empty string on failure. This is an offline method. Can be called before authorization. Can be called synchronously

Structs/GetFileMimeType.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: fileName
Structs/GetFileMimeType.html#/s:5TDLib15.abstract: The name of the file or path to the file

Structs/GetFileMimeType.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: init(fileName:)
Structs/GetFileMimeType.html#/s:5TDLib15.abstract: Returns the MIME type of a file, guessed by its extension. Returns an empty string on failure. This is an offline method. Can be called before authorization. Can be called synchronously

Structs/ParseTextEntities.html#/s:5TDLib.name: init(text:parseMode:)
Structs/ParseTextEntities.html#/s:5TDLib.abstract: Parses Bold, Italic, Underline, Strikethrough, Code, Pre, PreCode, TextUrl and MentionName entities contained in the text. This is an offline method. Can be called before authorization. Can be called synchronously

Structs/GetTextEntities.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: text
Structs/GetTextEntities.html#/s:5TDLib15.abstract: The text in which to look for entites

Structs/GetTextEntities.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: init(text:)
Structs/GetTextEntities.html#/s:5TDLib15.abstract: Returns all entities (mentions, hashtags, cashtags, bot commands, URLs, and email addresses) contained in the text. This is an offline method. Can be called before authorization. Can be called synchronously

Structs/EditMessageSchedulingState.html#.name: schedulingState
Structs/EditMessageSchedulingState.html#.abstract: The new message scheduling state. Pass null to send the message immediately

Structs/EditMessageSchedulingState.html#.name: init(chatId:messageId:schedulingState:)
Structs/EditMessageSchedulingState.html#.abstract: Edits the time when a scheduled message will be sent. Scheduling state of all messages in the same album or forwarded together with the message will be also changed

Structs/EditInlineMessageReplyMarkup.htm.name: init(inlineMessageId:replyMarkup:)
Structs/EditInlineMessageReplyMarkup.htm.abstract: Edits the reply markup of an inline message sent via a bot; for bots only

Structs/EditInlineMessageCaption.html#/s.name: init(inlineMessageId:replyMarkup:caption:)
Structs/EditInlineMessageCaption.html#/s.abstract: Edits the caption of an inline message sent via a bot; for bots only

Structs/EditInlineMessageMedia.html#/s:5.name: replyMarkup
Structs/EditInlineMessageMedia.html#/s:5.abstract: The new message reply markup; for bots only

Structs/EditInlineMessageMedia.html#/s:5.name: inputMessageContent
Structs/EditInlineMessageMedia.html#/s:5.abstract: New content of the message. Must be one of the following types: InputMessageAnimation, InputMessageAudio, InputMessageDocument, InputMessagePhoto or InputMessageVideo

Structs/EditInlineMessageMedia.html#/s:5.name: init(inlineMessageId:replyMarkup:inputMessageContent:)
Structs/EditInlineMessageMedia.html#/s:5.abstract: Edits the content of a message with an animation, an audio, a document, a photo or a video in an inline message sent via a bot; for bots only

Structs/EditInlineMessageLiveLocation.ht.name: location
Structs/EditInlineMessageLiveLocation.ht.abstract: New location content of the message; may be null. Pass null to stop sharing the live location

Structs/EditInlineMessageLiveLocation.ht.name: init(inlineMessageId:replyMarkup:location:)
Structs/EditInlineMessageLiveLocation.ht.abstract: Edits the content of a live location in an inline message sent via a bot; for bots only

Structs/EditInlineMessageText.html#/s:5T.name: inputMessageContent
Structs/EditInlineMessageText.html#/s:5T.abstract: New text content of the message. Should be of type InputMessageText

Structs/EditInlineMessageText.html#/s:5T.name: init(inlineMessageId:replyMarkup:inputMessageContent:)
Structs/EditInlineMessageText.html#/s:5T.abstract: Edits the text of an inline text or game message sent via a bot; for bots only

Structs/EditMessageReplyMarkup.html#/s:5.name: init(chatId:messageId:replyMarkup:)
Structs/EditMessageReplyMarkup.html#/s:5.abstract: Edits the message reply markup; for bots only. Returns the edited message after the edit is completed on the server side

Structs/EditMessageCaption.html#/s:5TDLi.name: replyMarkup
Structs/EditMessageCaption.html#/s:5TDLi.abstract: The new message reply markup; for bots only

Structs/EditMessageCaption.html#/s:5TDLi.name: init(chatId:messageId:replyMarkup:caption:)
Structs/EditMessageCaption.html#/s:5TDLi.abstract: Edits the message content caption. Returns the edited message after the edit is completed on the server side

Structs/EditMessageMedia.html#/s:5TDLib1.name: replyMarkup
Structs/EditMessageMedia.html#/s:5TDLib1.abstract: The new message reply markup; for bots only

Structs/EditMessageMedia.html#/s:5TDLib1.name: inputMessageContent
Structs/EditMessageMedia.html#/s:5TDLib1.abstract: New content of the message. Must be one of the following types: InputMessageAnimation, InputMessageAudio, InputMessageDocument, InputMessagePhoto or InputMessageVideo

Structs/EditMessageMedia.html#/s:5TDLib1.name: init(chatId:messageId:replyMarkup:inputMessageContent:)
Structs/EditMessageMedia.html#/s:5TDLib1.abstract: Edits the content of a message with an animation, an audio, a document, a photo or a video. The media in the message can’t be replaced if the message was set to self-destruct. Media can’t be replaced by self-destructing media. Media in an album can be edited only to contain a photo or a video. Returns the edited message after the edit is completed on the server side

Structs/EditMessageLiveLocation.html#/s:.name: replyMarkup
Structs/EditMessageLiveLocation.html#/s:.abstract: The new message reply markup; for bots only

Structs/EditMessageLiveLocation.html#/s:.name: location
Structs/EditMessageLiveLocation.html#/s:.abstract: New location content of the message; may be null. Pass null to stop sharing the live location

Structs/EditMessageLiveLocation.html#/s:.name: init(chatId:messageId:replyMarkup:location:)
Structs/EditMessageLiveLocation.html#/s:.abstract: Edits the message content of a live location. Messages can be edited for a limited period of time specified in the live location. Returns the edited message after the edit is completed on the server side

Structs/EditMessageText.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: replyMarkup
Structs/EditMessageText.html#/s:5TDLib15.abstract: The new message reply markup; for bots only

Structs/EditMessageText.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: inputMessageContent
Structs/EditMessageText.html#/s:5TDLib15.abstract: New text content of the message. Should be of type InputMessageText

Structs/EditMessageText.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: init(chatId:messageId:replyMarkup:inputMessageContent:)
Structs/EditMessageText.html#/s:5TDLib15.abstract: Edits the text of a message (or a text of a game message). Returns the edited message after the edit is completed on the server side

Structs/DeleteChatMessagesFromUser.html#.name: init(chatId:userId:)
Structs/DeleteChatMessagesFromUser.html#.abstract: Deletes all messages sent by the specified user to a chat. Supported only for supergroups; requires can_delete_messages administrator privileges

Structs/DeleteMessages.html#/s:5TDLib14D.name: messageIds
Structs/DeleteMessages.html#/s:5TDLib14D.abstract: Identifiers of the messages to be deleted

Structs/DeleteMessages.html#/s:5TDLib14D.abstract: Pass true to try to delete messages for all chat members. Always true for supergroups, channels and secret chats

Structs/AddLocalMessage.html#/s:5TDLib15.abstract: Identifier of the user who will be shown as the sender of the message; may be 0 for channel posts

Structs/AddLocalMessage.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: replyToMessageId
Structs/AddLocalMessage.html#/s:5TDLib15.abstract: Identifier of the message to reply to or 0

Structs/AddLocalMessage.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: disableNotification
Structs/AddLocalMessage.html#/s:5TDLib15.abstract: Pass true to disable notification for the message

Structs/AddLocalMessage.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: inputMessageContent
Structs/AddLocalMessage.html#/s:5TDLib15.abstract: The content of the message to be added

Structs/AddLocalMessage.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: init(chatId:senderUserId:replyToMessageId:disableNotification:inputMessageContent:)
Structs/AddLocalMessage.html#/s:5TDLib15.abstract: Adds a local message to a chat. The message is persistent across application restarts only if the message database is used. Returns the added message

Structs/SendChatScreenshotTakenNotificat.name: init(chatId:)

Structs/SendChatSetTtlMessage.html#/s:5T.name: init(chatId:ttl:)
