Structs/ResendMessages.html#/s:5TDLib14R.abstract: Identifiers of the messages to resend. Message identifiers must be in a strictly increasing order

Structs/ResendMessages.html#/s:5TDLib14R.name: init(chatId:messageIds:)
Structs/ResendMessages.html#/s:5TDLib14R.abstract: Resends messages which failed to send. Can be called only for messages for which messageSendingStateFailed.can_retry is true and after specified in messageSendingStateFailed.retry_after time passed. -If a message is re-sent, the corresponding failed to send message is deleted. Returns the sent messages in the same order as the message identifiers passed in message_ids. If a message can’t be re-sent, null will be returned instead of the message

Structs/ForwardMessages.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: chatId
Structs/ForwardMessages.html#/s:5TDLib15.abstract: Identifier of the chat to which to forward messages

Structs/ForwardMessages.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: fromChatId
Structs/ForwardMessages.html#/s:5TDLib15.abstract: Identifier of the chat from which to forward messages

Structs/ForwardMessages.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: options
Structs/ForwardMessages.html#/s:5TDLib15.abstract: Options to be used to send the messages

Structs/ForwardMessages.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: asAlbum
Structs/ForwardMessages.html#/s:5TDLib15.abstract: True, if the messages should be grouped into an album after forwarding. For this to work, no more than 10 messages may be forwarded, and all of them must be photo or video messages

Structs/ForwardMessages.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: sendCopy
Structs/ForwardMessages.html#/s:5TDLib15.abstract: True, if content of the messages needs to be copied without links to the original messages. Always true if the messages are forwarded to a secret chat

Structs/ForwardMessages.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: removeCaption
Structs/ForwardMessages.html#/s:5TDLib15.abstract: True, if media captions of message copies needs to be removed. Ignored if send_copy is false

Structs/ForwardMessages.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: init(chatId:fromChatId:messageIds:options:asAlbum:sendCopy:removeCaption:)
Structs/ForwardMessages.html#/s:5TDLib15.abstract: Forwards previously sent messages. Returns the forwarded messages in the same order as the message identifiers passed in message_ids. If a message can’t be forwarded, null will be returned instead of the message

Structs/SendInlineQueryResultMessage.htm.name: replyToMessageId
Structs/SendInlineQueryResultMessage.htm.abstract: Identifier of a message to reply to or 0

Structs/SendInlineQueryResultMessage.htm.name: options
Structs/SendInlineQueryResultMessage.htm.abstract: Options to be used to send the message

Structs/SendInlineQueryResultMessage.htm.name: hideViaBot
Structs/SendInlineQueryResultMessage.htm.abstract: If true, there will be no mention of a bot, via which the message is sent. Can be used only for bots GetOption(“animation_search_bot_username”), GetOption(“photo_search_bot_username”) and GetOption(“venue_search_bot_username”)

Structs/SendInlineQueryResultMessage.htm.name: init(chatId:replyToMessageId:options:queryId:resultId:hideViaBot:)
Structs/SendInlineQueryResultMessage.htm.abstract: Sends the result of an inline query as a message. Returns the sent message. Always clears a chat draft message

Structs/SendBotStartMessage.html#/s:5TDL.name: parameter
Structs/SendBotStartMessage.html#/s:5TDL.abstract: A hidden parameter sent to the bot for deep linking purposes (https://core.telegram.org/bots#deep-linking)

Structs/SendBotStartMessage.html#/s:5TDL.name: init(botUserId:chatId:parameter:)
Structs/SendBotStartMessage.html#/s:5TDL.abstract: Invites a bot to a chat (if it is not yet a member) and sends it the /start command. Bots can’t be invited to a private chat other than the chat with the bot. Bots can’t be invited to channels (although they can be added as admins) and secret chats. Returns the sent message

Structs/SendMessageAlbum.html#/s:5TDLib1.name: replyToMessageId
Structs/SendMessageAlbum.html#/s:5TDLib1.abstract: Identifier of a message to reply to or 0

Structs/SendMessageAlbum.html#/s:5TDLib1.name: options
Structs/SendMessageAlbum.html#/s:5TDLib1.abstract: Options to be used to send the messages

Structs/SendMessageAlbum.html#/s:5TDLib1.name: init(chatId:replyToMessageId:options:inputMessageContents:)
Structs/SendMessageAlbum.html#/s:5TDLib1.abstract: Sends messages grouped together into an album. Currently only photo and video messages can be grouped into an album. Returns sent messages

Structs/SendMessage.html#/s:5TDLib11Send.name: replyToMessageId
Structs/SendMessage.html#/s:5TDLib11Send.abstract: Identifier of the message to reply to or 0

Structs/SendMessage.html#/s:5TDLib11Send.name: options
Structs/SendMessage.html#/s:5TDLib11Send.abstract: Options to be used to send the message

Structs/SendMessage.html#/s:5TDLib11Send.name: replyMarkup
Structs/SendMessage.html#/s:5TDLib11Send.abstract: Markup for replying to the message; for bots only

Structs/SendMessage.html#/s:5TDLib11Send.name: inputMessageContent
Structs/SendMessage.html#/s:5TDLib11Send.abstract: The content of the message to be sent

Structs/SendMessage.html#/s:5TDLib11Send.name: init(chatId:replyToMessageId:options:replyMarkup:inputMessageContent:)
Structs/SendMessage.html#/s:5TDLib11Send.abstract: Sends a message. Returns the sent message

Structs/GetMessageLinkInfo.html#/s:5TDLi.name: url
Structs/GetMessageLinkInfo.html#/s:5TDLi.abstract: The message link in the format “https://t.me/c/...”, or “tg://privatepost?…”, or “https://t.me/username/...”, or “tg://resolve?…”

Structs/GetMessageLinkInfo.html#/s:5TDLi.name: init(url:)
Structs/GetMessageLinkInfo.html#/s:5TDLi.abstract: Returns information about a public or private message link

Structs/GetMessageLink.html#/s:5TDLib14G.name: chatId
Structs/GetMessageLink.html#/s:5TDLib14G.abstract: Identifier of the chat to which the message belongs

Structs/GetMessageLink.html#/s:5TDLib14G.name: init(chatId:messageId:)
Structs/GetMessageLink.html#/s:5TDLib14G.abstract: Returns a private HTTPS link to a message in a chat. Available only for already sent messages in supergroups and channels. The link will work only for members of the chat

Structs/GetPublicMessageLink.html#/s:5TD.name: chatId
Structs/GetPublicMessageLink.html#/s:5TD.abstract: Identifier of the chat to which the message belongs

Structs/GetPublicMessageLink.html#/s:5TD.name: forAlbum
Structs/GetPublicMessageLink.html#/s:5TD.abstract: Pass true if a link for a whole media album should be returned

Structs/GetPublicMessageLink.html#/s:5TD.name: init(chatId:messageId:forAlbum:)
Structs/GetPublicMessageLink.html#/s:5TD.abstract: Returns a public HTTPS link to a message. Available only for messages in supergroups and channels with a username

Structs/RemoveNotificationGroup.html#/s:.name: init(notificationGroupId:maxNotificationId:)
Structs/RemoveNotificationGroup.html#/s:.abstract: Removes a group of active notifications. Needs to be called only if the notification group is removed by the current user

Structs/RemoveNotification.html#/s:5TDLi.name: notificationGroupId
Structs/RemoveNotification.html#/s:5TDLi.abstract: Identifier of notification group to which the notification belongs

Structs/RemoveNotification.html#/s:5TDLi.name: init(notificationGroupId:notificationId:)
Structs/RemoveNotification.html#/s:5TDLi.abstract: Removes an active notification from notification list. Needs to be called only if the notification is removed by the current user

Structs/GetChatScheduledMessages.html#/s.name: init(chatId:)
Structs/GetChatScheduledMessages.html#/s.abstract: Returns all scheduled messages in a chat. The messages are returned in a reverse chronological order (i.e., in order of decreasing message_id)

Structs/GetChatMessageCount.html#/s:5TDL.name: chatId
Structs/GetChatMessageCount.html#/s:5TDL.abstract: Identifier of the chat in which to count messages

Structs/GetChatMessageCount.html#/s:5TDL.name: filter
Structs/GetChatMessageCount.html#/s:5TDL.abstract: Filter for message content; searchMessagesFilterEmpty is unsupported in this function

Structs/GetChatMessageCount.html#/s:5TDL.name: returnLocal
Structs/GetChatMessageCount.html#/s:5TDL.abstract: If true, returns count that is available locally without sending network requests, returning -1 if the number of messages is unknown

Structs/GetChatMessageCount.html#/s:5TDL.name: init(chatId:filter:returnLocal:)
Structs/GetChatMessageCount.html#/s:5TDL.abstract: Returns approximate number of messages of the specified type in the chat

Structs/GetChatMessageByDate.html#/s:5TD.name: date
Structs/GetChatMessageByDate.html#/s:5TD.abstract: Point in time (Unix timestamp) relative to which to search for messages

Structs/GetChatMessageByDate.html#/s:5TD.name: init(chatId:date:)
Structs/GetChatMessageByDate.html#/s:5TD.abstract: Returns the last message sent in a chat no later than the specified date

Structs/GetActiveLiveLocationMessages.ht.name: init()
Structs/GetActiveLiveLocationMessages.ht.abstract: Returns all active live locations that should be updated by the client. The list is persistent across application restarts only if the message database is used

Structs/SearchChatRecentLocationMessages.name: limit
Structs/SearchChatRecentLocationMessages.abstract: The maximum number of messages to be returned

Structs/SearchChatRecentLocationMessages.name: init(chatId:limit:)
Structs/SearchChatRecentLocationMessages.abstract: Returns information about the recent locations of chat members that were sent to the chat. Returns up to 1 location message per user

Structs/SearchCallMessages.html#/s:5TDLi.name: fromMessageId
Structs/SearchCallMessages.html#/s:5TDLi.abstract: Identifier of the message from which to search; use 0 to get results from the last message

Structs/SearchCallMessages.html#/s:5TDLi.name: limit
Structs/SearchCallMessages.html#/s:5TDLi.abstract: The maximum number of messages to be returned; up to 100. Fewer messages may be returned than specified by the limit, even if the end of the message history has not been reached

Structs/SearchCallMessages.html#/s:5TDLi.name: onlyMissed
Structs/SearchCallMessages.html#/s:5TDLi.abstract: If true, returns only messages with missed calls

Structs/SearchCallMessages.html#/s:5TDLi.name: init(fromMessageId:limit:onlyMissed:)
Structs/SearchCallMessages.html#/s:5TDLi.abstract: Searches for call messages. Returns the results in reverse chronological order (i. e., in order of decreasing message_id). For optimal performance the number of returned messages is chosen by the library

Structs/SearchSecretMessages.html#/s:5TD.name: chatId
Structs/SearchSecretMessages.html#/s:5TD.abstract: Identifier of the chat in which to search. Specify 0 to search in all secret chats

Structs/SearchSecretMessages.html#/s:5TD.name: query
Structs/SearchSecretMessages.html#/s:5TD.abstract: Query to search for. If empty, searchChatMessages should be used instead

Structs/SearchSecretMessages.html#/s:5TD.name: fromSearchId
Structs/SearchSecretMessages.html#/s:5TD.abstract: The identifier from the result of a previous request, use 0 to get results from the last message

Structs/SearchSecretMessages.html#/s:5TD.name: limit
Structs/SearchSecretMessages.html#/s:5TD.abstract: The maximum number of messages to be returned; up to 100. Fewer messages may be returned than specified by the limit, even if the end of the message history has not been reached

Structs/SearchSecretMessages.html#/s:5TD.name: filter
Structs/SearchSecretMessages.html#/s:5TD.abstract: A filter for the content of messages in the search results

Structs/SearchSecretMessages.html#/s:5TD.name: init(chatId:query:fromSearchId:limit:filter:)
Structs/SearchSecretMessages.html#/s:5TD.abstract: Searches for messages in secret chats. Returns the results in reverse chronological order. For optimal performance the number of returned messages is chosen by the library

Structs/SearchMessages.html#/s:5TDLib14S.name: chatList
Structs/SearchMessages.html#/s:5TDLib14S.abstract: Chat list in which to search messages; pass null to search in all chats regardless of their chat list

Structs/SearchMessages.html#/s:5TDLib14S.name: offsetDate
Structs/SearchMessages.html#/s:5TDLib14S.abstract: The date of the message starting from which the results should be fetched. Use 0 or any date in the future to get results from the last message

Structs/SearchMessages.html#/s:5TDLib14S.name: offsetChatId
Structs/SearchMessages.html#/s:5TDLib14S.abstract: The chat identifier of the last found message, or 0 for the first request

Structs/SearchMessages.html#/s:5TDLib14S.name: offsetMessageId
Structs/SearchMessages.html#/s:5TDLib14S.abstract: The message identifier of the last found message, or 0 for the first request

Structs/SearchMessages.html#/s:5TDLib14S.name: limit
Structs/SearchMessages.html#/s:5TDLib14S.abstract: The maximum number of messages to be returned, up to 100. Fewer messages may be returned than specified by the limit, even if the end of the message history has not been reached

Structs/SearchMessages.html#/s:5TDLib14S.name: init(chatList:query:offsetDate:offsetChatId:offsetMessageId:limit:)
Structs/SearchMessages.html#/s:5TDLib14S.abstract: Searches for messages in all chats except secret chats. Returns the results in reverse chronological order (i.e., in order of decreasing (date, chat_id, message_id)). -For optimal performance the number of returned messages is chosen by the library

Structs/SearchChatMessages.html#/s:5TDLi.name: chatId
Structs/SearchChatMessages.html#/s:5TDLi.abstract: Identifier of the chat in which to search messages

Structs/SearchChatMessages.html#/s:5TDLi.name: senderUserId
Structs/SearchChatMessages.html#/s:5TDLi.abstract: If not 0, only messages sent by the specified user will be returned. Not supported in secret chats

Structs/SearchChatMessages.html#/s:5TDLi.name: fromMessageId
Structs/SearchChatMessages.html#/s:5TDLi.abstract: Identifier of the message starting from which history must be fetched; use 0 to get results from the last message

Structs/SearchChatMessages.html#/s:5TDLi.name: offset
Structs/SearchChatMessages.html#/s:5TDLi.abstract: Specify 0 to get results from exactly the from_message_id or a negative offset to get the specified message and some newer messages

Structs/SearchChatMessages.html#/s:5TDLi.name: limit
Structs/SearchChatMessages.html#/s:5TDLi.abstract: The maximum number of messages to be returned; must be positive and can’t be greater than 100. If the offset is negative, the limit must be greater than -offset. Fewer messages may be returned than specified by the limit, even if the end of the message history has not been reached

Structs/SearchChatMessages.html#/s:5TDLi.name: filter
Structs/SearchChatMessages.html#/s:5TDLi.abstract: Filter for message content in the search results

Structs/SearchChatMessages.html#/s:5TDLi.name: init(chatId:query:senderUserId:fromMessageId:offset:limit:filter:)
Structs/SearchChatMessages.html#/s:5TDLi.abstract: Searches for messages with given words in the chat. Returns the results in reverse chronological order, i.e. in order of decreasing message_id. Cannot be used in secret chats with a non-empty query -(searchSecretMessages should be used instead), or without an enabled message database. For optimal performance the number of returned messages is chosen by the library

Structs/DeleteChatHistory.html#/s:5TDLib.name: removeFromChatList
Structs/DeleteChatHistory.html#/s:5TDLib.abstract: Pass true if the chat should be removed from the chat list

Structs/DeleteChatHistory.html#/s:5TDLib.name: revoke
Structs/DeleteChatHistory.html#/s:5TDLib.abstract: Pass true to try to delete chat history for all users

Structs/DeleteChatHistory.html#/s:5TDLib.name: init(chatId:removeFromChatList:revoke:)
Structs/DeleteChatHistory.html#/s:5TDLib.abstract: Deletes all messages in the chat. Use Chat.can_be_deleted_only_for_self and Chat.can_be_deleted_for_all_users fields to find whether and how the method can be applied to the chat

Structs/GetChatHistory.html#/s:5TDLib14G.name: fromMessageId
Structs/GetChatHistory.html#/s:5TDLib14G.abstract: Identifier of the message starting from which history must be fetched; use 0 to get results from the last message

Structs/GetChatHistory.html#/s:5TDLib14G.name: offset
Structs/GetChatHistory.html#/s:5TDLib14G.abstract: Specify 0 to get results from exactly the from_message_id or a negative offset up to 99 to get additionally some newer messages

Structs/GetChatHistory.html#/s:5TDLib14G.name: limit
Structs/GetChatHistory.html#/s:5TDLib14G.abstract: The maximum number of messages to be returned; must be positive and can’t be greater than 100. If the offset is negative, the limit must be greater or equal to -offset. Fewer messages may be returned than specified by the limit, even if the end of the message history has not been reached

Structs/GetChatHistory.html#/s:5TDLib14G.name: onlyLocal
Structs/GetChatHistory.html#/s:5TDLib14G.abstract: If true, returns only messages that are available locally without sending network requests

Structs/GetChatHistory.html#/s:5TDLib14G.name: init(chatId:fromMessageId:offset:limit:onlyLocal:)
Structs/GetChatHistory.html#/s:5TDLib14G.abstract: Returns messages in a chat. The messages are returned in a reverse chronological order (i.e., in order of decreasing message_id). -For optimal performance the number of returned messages is chosen by the library. This is an offline request if only_local is true

Structs/GetGroupsInCommon.html#/s:5TDLib.name: offsetChatId
Structs/GetGroupsInCommon.html#/s:5TDLib.abstract: Chat identifier starting from which to return chats; use 0 for the first request

Structs/GetGroupsInCommon.html#/s:5TDLib.name: limit
Structs/GetGroupsInCommon.html#/s:5TDLib.abstract: The maximum number of chats to be returned; up to 100

Structs/GetGroupsInCommon.html#/s:5TDLib.name: init(userId:offsetChatId:limit:)
Structs/GetGroupsInCommon.html#/s:5TDLib.abstract: Returns a list of common group chats with a given user. Chats are sorted by their type and creation date

Structs/GetInactiveSupergroupChats.html#.name: init()
Structs/GetInactiveSupergroupChats.html#.abstract: Returns a list of recently inactive supergroups and channels. Can be used when user reaches limit on the number of joined supergroups and channels and receives CHANNELS_TOO_MUCH error

Structs/GetSuitableDiscussionChats.html#.name: init()
Structs/GetSuitableDiscussionChats.html#.abstract: Returns a list of basic group and supergroup chats, which can be used as a discussion group for a channel. Basic group chats need to be first upgraded to supergroups before they can be set as a discussion group

Structs/CheckCreatedPublicChatsLimit.htm.name: type
Structs/CheckCreatedPublicChatsLimit.htm.abstract: Type of the public chats, for which to check the limit

Structs/CheckCreatedPublicChatsLimit.htm.name: init(type:)
Structs/CheckCreatedPublicChatsLimit.htm.abstract: Checks whether the maximum number of owned public chats has been reached. Returns corresponding error if the limit was reached

Structs/GetCreatedPublicChats.html#/s:5T.name: type
Structs/GetCreatedPublicChats.html#/s:5T.abstract: Type of the public chats to return

Structs/GetCreatedPublicChats.html#/s:5T.name: init(type:)
Structs/GetCreatedPublicChats.html#/s:5T.abstract: Returns a list of public chats of the specified type, owned by the user

Structs/CheckChatUsername.html#/s:5TDLib.name: chatId
Structs/CheckChatUsername.html#/s:5TDLib.abstract: Chat identifier; should be identifier of a supergroup chat, or a channel chat, or a private chat with self, or zero if chat is being created

Structs/CheckChatUsername.html#/s:5TDLib.name: init(chatId:username:)
Structs/CheckChatUsername.html#/s:5TDLib.abstract: Checks whether a username can be set for a chat

Structs/ClearRecentlyFoundChats.html#/s:.name: init()
Structs/ClearRecentlyFoundChats.html#/s:.abstract: Clears the list of recently found chats

Structs/RemoveRecentlyFoundChat.html#/s:.name: chatId
Structs/RemoveRecentlyFoundChat.html#/s:.abstract: Identifier of the chat to be removed

Structs/RemoveRecentlyFoundChat.html#/s:.name: init(chatId:)
Structs/RemoveRecentlyFoundChat.html#/s:.abstract: Removes a chat from the list of recently found chats

Structs/AddRecentlyFoundChat.html#/s:5TD.name: init(chatId:)
Structs/AddRecentlyFoundChat.html#/s:5TD.abstract: Adds a chat to the list of recently found chats. The chat is added to the beginning of the list. If the chat is already in the list, it will be removed from the list first

Structs/RemoveTopChat.html#/s:5TDLib13Re.name: init(category:chatId:)
Structs/RemoveTopChat.html#/s:5TDLib13Re.abstract: Removes a chat from the list of frequently used chats. Supported only if the chat info database is enabled

Structs/GetTopChats.html#/s:5TDLib11GetT.name: limit
Structs/GetTopChats.html#/s:5TDLib11GetT.abstract: The maximum number of chats to be returned; up to 30

Structs/GetTopChats.html#/s:5TDLib11GetT.name: init(category:limit:)
Structs/GetTopChats.html#/s:5TDLib11GetT.abstract: Returns a list of frequently used chats. Supported only if the chat info database is enabled

Structs/SearchChatsNearby.html#/s:5TDLib.name: init(location:)
Structs/SearchChatsNearby.html#/s:5TDLib.abstract: Returns a list of users and location-based supergroups nearby. The list of users nearby will be updated for 60 seconds after the request by the updates updateUsersNearby. The request should be sent again every 25 seconds with adjusted location to not miss new chats

Structs/SearchChatsOnServer.html#/s:5TDL.name: limit
Structs/SearchChatsOnServer.html#/s:5TDL.abstract: The maximum number of chats to be returned

Structs/SearchChatsOnServer.html#/s:5TDL.name: init(query:limit:)
Structs/SearchChatsOnServer.html#/s:5TDL.abstract: Searches for the specified query in the title and username of already known chats via request to the server. Returns chats in the order seen in the chat list

Structs/SearchChats.html#/s:5TDLib11Sear.name: query
Structs/SearchChats.html#/s:5TDLib11Sear.abstract: Query to search for. If the query is empty, returns up to 20 recently found chats

Structs/SearchChats.html#/s:5TDLib11Sear.name: limit
Structs/SearchChats.html#/s:5TDLib11Sear.abstract: The maximum number of chats to be returned

Structs/SearchChats.html#/s:5TDLib11Sear.name: init(query:limit:)
Structs/SearchChats.html#/s:5TDLib11Sear.abstract: Searches for the specified query in the title and username of already known chats, this is an offline request. Returns chats in the order seen in the chat list

Structs/SearchPublicChats.html#/s:5TDLib.name: init(query:)
Structs/SearchPublicChats.html#/s:5TDLib.abstract: Searches public chats by looking for specified query in their username and title. Currently only private chats, supergroups and channels can be public. Returns a meaningful number of results. Returns nothing if the length of the searched username prefix is less than 5. Excludes private chats with contacts and chats from the chat list from the results

Structs/SearchPublicChat.html#/s:5TDLib1.name: init(username:)
Structs/SearchPublicChat.html#/s:5TDLib1.abstract: Searches a public chat by its username. Currently only private chats, supergroups and channels can be public. Returns the chat if found; otherwise an error is returned

Structs/GetChats.html#/s:5TDLib8GetChats.name: chatList
Structs/GetChats.html#/s:5TDLib8GetChats.abstract: The chat list in which to return chats

Structs/GetChats.html#/s:5TDLib8GetChats.name: limit
Structs/GetChats.html#/s:5TDLib8GetChats.abstract: The maximum number of chats to be returned. It is possible that fewer chats than the limit are returned even if the end of the list is not reached

Structs/GetChats.html#/s:5TDLib8GetChats.name: init(chatList:offsetOrder:offsetChatId:limit:)
Structs/GetChats.html#/s:5TDLib8GetChats.abstract: Returns an ordered list of chats in a chat list. Chats are sorted by the pair (order, chat_id) in decreasing order. (For example, to get a list of chats from the beginning, the offset_order should be equal to a biggest signed 64-bit number 9223372036854775807 == 2^63 - 1). -For optimal performance the number of returned chats is chosen by the library

Structs/GetRemoteFile.html#/s:5TDLib13Ge.name: remoteFileId
Structs/GetRemoteFile.html#/s:5TDLib13Ge.abstract: Remote identifier of the file to get

Structs/GetRemoteFile.html#/s:5TDLib13Ge.name: init(remoteFileId:fileType:)
Structs/GetRemoteFile.html#/s:5TDLib13Ge.abstract: Returns information about a file by its remote ID; this is an offline request. Can be used to register a URL as a file for further uploading, or sending as a message. Even the request succeeds, the file can be used only if it is still accessible to the user. -For example, if the file is from a message, then the message must be not deleted and accessible to the user. If the file database is disabled, then the corresponding object with the file must be preloaded by the client

Structs/GetFile.html#/s:5TDLib7GetFileV6.name: init(fileId:)
Structs/GetFile.html#/s:5TDLib7GetFileV6.abstract: Returns information about a file; this is an offline request

Structs/GetMessages.html#/s:5TDLib11GetM.name: chatId
Structs/GetMessages.html#/s:5TDLib11GetM.abstract: Identifier of the chat the messages belong to

Structs/GetMessages.html#/s:5TDLib11GetM.name: init(chatId:messageIds:)
Structs/GetMessages.html#/s:5TDLib11GetM.abstract: Returns information about messages. If a message is not found, returns null on the corresponding position of the result

Structs/GetChatPinnedMessage.html#/s:5TD.name: chatId
Structs/GetChatPinnedMessage.html#/s:5TD.abstract: Identifier of the chat the message belongs to

Structs/GetChatPinnedMessage.html#/s:5TD.name: init(chatId:)
Structs/GetChatPinnedMessage.html#/s:5TD.abstract: Returns information about a pinned chat message

Structs/GetRepliedMessage.html#/s:5TDLib.name: chatId
Structs/GetRepliedMessage.html#/s:5TDLib.abstract: Identifier of the chat the message belongs to

Structs/GetRepliedMessage.html#/s:5TDLib.name: messageId
Structs/GetRepliedMessage.html#/s:5TDLib.abstract: Identifier of the message reply to which get

Structs/GetRepliedMessage.html#/s:5TDLib.name: init(chatId:messageId:)
Structs/GetRepliedMessage.html#/s:5TDLib.abstract: Returns information about a message that is replied by given message

Structs/GetMessageLocally.html#/s:5TDLib.name: chatId
Structs/GetMessageLocally.html#/s:5TDLib.abstract: Identifier of the chat the message belongs to

Structs/GetMessageLocally.html#/s:5TDLib.name: init(chatId:messageId:)
Structs/GetMessageLocally.html#/s:5TDLib.abstract: Returns information about a message, if it is available locally without sending network request. This is an offline request

Structs/GetMessage.html#/s:5TDLib10GetMe.name: chatId

Structs/Message.html#/s:5TDLib7MessageV1.name: schedulingState

Structs/Message.html#/s:5TDLib7MessageV1.name: canBeEdited
Structs/Message.html#/s:5TDLib7MessageV1.abstract: True, if the message can be edited. For live location and poll messages this fields shows whether editMessageLiveLocation or stopPoll can be used with this message by the client

Structs/Message.html#/s:5TDLib7MessageV1.name: canBeForwarded
Structs/Message.html#/s:5TDLib7MessageV1.abstract: True, if the message can be forwarded

Structs/Message.html#/s:5TDLib7MessageV2.name: canBeDeletedOnlyForSelf
Structs/Message.html#/s:5TDLib7MessageV2.abstract: True, if the message can be deleted only for the current user while other users will continue to see it

Structs/Message.html#/s:5TDLib7MessageV2.name: canBeDeletedForAllUsers
Structs/Message.html#/s:5TDLib7MessageV2.abstract: True, if the message can be deleted for all users

Structs/Message.html#/s:5TDLib7MessageV1.name: isChannelPost
Structs/Message.html#/s:5TDLib7MessageV1.abstract: True, if the message is a channel post. All messages to channels are channel posts, all other messages are not channel posts

Structs/Message.html#/s:5TDLib7MessageV2.name: containsUnreadMention
Structs/Message.html#/s:5TDLib7MessageV2.abstract: True, if the message contains an unread mention for the current user

Structs/Message.html#/s:5TDLib7MessageV4.name: date
Structs/Message.html#/s:5TDLib7MessageV4.abstract: Point in time (Unix timestamp) when the message was sent

Structs/Message.html#/s:5TDLib7MessageV8.name: editDate
Structs/Message.html#/s:5TDLib7MessageV8.abstract: Point in time (Unix timestamp) when the message was last edited

Structs/Message.html#/s:5TDLib7MessageV0.name: replyToMessageId
Structs/Message.html#/s:5TDLib7MessageV0.abstract: If non-zero, the identifier of the message this message is replying to; can be the identifier of a deleted message

Structs/Message.html#/s:5TDLib7MessageV3.name: ttl
Structs/Message.html#/s:5TDLib7MessageV3.abstract: For self-destructing messages, the message’s TTL (Time To Live), in seconds; 0 if none. TDLib will send updateDeleteMessages or updateMessageContent once the TTL expires

Structs/Message.html#/s:5TDLib7MessageV1.name: ttlExpiresIn
Structs/Message.html#/s:5TDLib7MessageV1.abstract: Time left before the message expires, in seconds

Structs/Message.html#/s:5TDLib7MessageV1.name: viaBotUserId

Structs/Message.html#/s:5TDLib7MessageV5.name: views

Structs/Message.html#/s:5TDLib7MessageV1.name: mediaAlbumId
Structs/Message.html#/s:5TDLib7MessageV1.abstract: Unique identifier of an album this message belongs to. Only photos and videos can be grouped together in albums

Structs/Message.html#/s:5TDLib7MessageV1.name: restrictionReason
Structs/Message.html#/s:5TDLib7MessageV1.abstract: If non-empty, contains a human-readable description of the reason why access to this message must be restricted

Structs/Message.html#/s:5TDLib7MessageV1.name: replyMarkup
Structs/Message.html#/s:5TDLib7MessageV1.abstract: Reply markup for the message; may be null

Structs/MessageForwardInfo.html#/s:5TDLi.name: date

Structs/MessageForwardInfo.html#/s:5TDLi.name: fromChatId

Structs/MessageForwardInfo.html#/s:5TDLi.name: fromMessageId
Structs/MessageForwardInfo.html#/s:5TDLi.abstract: For messages forwarded to the chat with the current user (Saved Messages) or to the channel’s discussion group, the identifier of the original message from which the new message was forwarded last time; 0 if unknown

Structs/SecretChat.html#/s:5TDLib10Secre.name: isOutbound
Structs/SecretChat.html#/s:5TDLib10Secre.abstract: True, if the chat was created by the current user; otherwise false

Structs/SecretChat.html#/s:5TDLib10Secre.name: ttl
Structs/SecretChat.html#/s:5TDLib10Secre.abstract: Current message Time To Live setting (self-destruct timer) for the chat, in seconds

Structs/SecretChat.html#/s:5TDLib10Secre.name: keyHash
Structs/SecretChat.html#/s:5TDLib10Secre.abstract: Hash of the currently used key for comparison with the hash of the chat partner’s key. This is a string of 36 little-endian bytes, which must be split into groups of 2 bits, each denoting a pixel of one of 4 colors FFFFFF, D5E6F3, 2D5775, and 2F99C9. -The pixels must be used to make a 12x12 square image filled from left to right, top to bottom. Alternatively, the first 32 bytes of the hash can be converted to the hexadecimal format and printed as 32 2-digit hex numbers

Structs/SecretChat.html#/s:5TDLib10Secre.name: layer
Structs/SecretChat.html#/s:5TDLib10Secre.abstract: Secret chat layer; determines features supported by the other client. Video notes are supported if the layer >= 66; nested text entities and underline and strikethrough entities are supported if the layer >= 101

Structs/SupergroupFullInfo.html#/s:5TDLi.name: description
Structs/SupergroupFullInfo.html#/s:5TDLi.abstract: Supergroup or channel description

Structs/SupergroupFullInfo.html#/s:5TDLi.name: memberCount
Structs/SupergroupFullInfo.html#/s:5TDLi.abstract: Number of members in the supergroup or channel; 0 if unknown

Structs/SupergroupFullInfo.html#/s:5TDLi.name: administratorCount
Structs/SupergroupFullInfo.html#/s:5TDLi.abstract: Number of privileged users in the supergroup or channel; 0 if unknown

Structs/SupergroupFullInfo.html#/s:5TDLi.name: restrictedCount

Structs/SupergroupFullInfo.html#/s:5TDLi.name: bannedCount

Structs/SupergroupFullInfo.html#/s:5TDLi.name: canSetUsername
Structs/SupergroupFullInfo.html#/s:5TDLi.abstract: True, if the chat username can be changed

In public or discussion groups and both public and private channels, old messages are always available, so this option affects only private supergroups without a linked chat. Structs/SupergroupFullInfo.html#/s:5TDLi.abstract: Identifier of the supergroup sticker set; 0 if none

Structs/SupergroupFullInfo.html#/s:5TDLi.name: upgradedFromMaxMessageId
Structs/SupergroupFullInfo.html#/s:5TDLi.abstract: Identifier of the last message in the basic group from which supergroup was upgraded; 0 if none
Contains full information about a supergroup or channel

Structs/Supergroup.html#/s:5TDLib10Super.name: isSlowModeEnabled

Structs/Supergroup.html#/s:5TDLib10Super.name: isChannel

Structs/Supergroup.html#/s:5TDLib10Super.name: isVerified

Structs/Supergroup.html#/s:5TDLib10Super.name: restrictionReason

Structs/Supergroup.html#/s:5TDLib10Super.name: isScam

Structs/Supergroup.html#/s:5TDLib10Super.abstract: Represents a supergroup or channel with zero or more members (subscribers in the case of channels). From the point of view of the system, a channel is a special kind of a supergroup: only administrators can post and see the list of members, and posts from all administrators use the name and photo of the channel instead of individual names and profile photos. Unlike supergroups, channels can have an unlimited number of subscribers

Structs/Document.html#/s:5TDLib8Document.abstract: MIME type of the file; as defined by the sender

Structs/Document.html#/s:5TDLib8Document.name: thumbnail
Structs/Document.html#/s:5TDLib8Document.abstract: Document thumbnail in JPEG or PNG format (PNG will be used only for background patterns); as defined by the sender; may be null

Structs/Audio.html#/s:5TDLib5AudioV8dura.name: duration
Structs/Audio.html#/s:5TDLib5AudioV8dura.abstract: Duration of the audio, in seconds; as defined by the sender

Structs/Audio.html#/s:5TDLib5AudioV5titl.name: title
Structs/Audio.html#/s:5TDLib5AudioV5titl.abstract: Title of the audio; as defined by the sender

Structs/Audio.html#/s:5TDLib5AudioV9perf.name: performer
Structs/Audio.html#/s:5TDLib5AudioV9perf.abstract: Performer of the audio; as defined by the sender

Structs/Audio.html#/s:5TDLib5AudioV8file.name: fileName
Structs/Audio.html#/s:5TDLib5AudioV8file.abstract: Original name of the file; as defined by the sender

Structs/Audio.html#/s:5TDLib5AudioV8mime.name: mimeType
Structs/Audio.html#/s:5TDLib5AudioV8mime.abstract: The MIME type of the file; as defined by the sender

Structs/Audio.html#/s:5TDLib5AudioV23alb.name: albumCoverMinithumbnail
Structs/Audio.html#/s:5TDLib5AudioV23alb.abstract: The minithumbnail of the album cover; may be null

Structs/Audio.html#/s:5TDLib5AudioV19alb.name: albumCoverThumbnail
Structs/Audio.html#/s:5TDLib5AudioV19alb.abstract: The thumbnail of the album cover; as defined by the sender. The full size thumbnail should be extracted from the downloaded file; may be null

Structs/Audio.html#/s:5TDLib5AudioV8dura.name: init(duration:title:performer:fileName:mimeType:albumCoverMinithumbnail:albumCoverThumbnail:audio:)
Structs/Audio.html#/s:5TDLib5AudioV8dura.abstract: Describes an audio file. Audio is usually in MP3 or M4A format

Structs/Animation.html#/s:5TDLib9Animati.name: duration
Structs/Animation.html#/s:5TDLib9Animati.abstract: Duration of the animation, in seconds; as defined by the sender

Structs/Animation.html#/s:5TDLib9Animati.name: fileName
Structs/Animation.html#/s:5TDLib9Animati.abstract: Original name of the file; as defined by the sender

Structs/Animation.html#/s:5TDLib9Animati.name: mimeType
Structs/Animation.html#/s:5TDLib9Animati.abstract: MIME type of the file, usually “image/gif” or “video/mp4”

Structs/Animation.html#/s:5TDLib9Animati.name: init(duration:width:height:fileName:mimeType:minithumbnail:thumbnail:animation:)
Structs/Animation.html#/s:5TDLib9Animati.abstract: Describes an animation file. The animation must be encoded in GIF or MPEG4 format

Structs/PollOption.html#/s:5TDLib10PollO.name: voterCount
Structs/PollOption.html#/s:5TDLib10PollO.abstract: Number of voters for this option, available only for closed or voted polls

Structs/PollOption.html#/s:5TDLib10PollO.name: votePercentage
Structs/PollOption.html#/s:5TDLib10PollO.abstract: The percentage of votes for this option, 0-100

Structs/PollOption.html#/s:5TDLib10PollO.name: isChosen
Structs/PollOption.html#/s:5TDLib10PollO.abstract: True, if the option was chosen by the user

Structs/PollOption.html#/s:5TDLib10PollO.name: isBeingChosen
Structs/PollOption.html#/s:5TDLib10PollO.abstract: True, if the option is being chosen by a pending setPollAnswer request

Structs/PollOption.html#/s:5TDLib10PollO.name: init(text:voterCount:votePercentage:isChosen:isBeingChosen:)
Structs/PollOption.html#/s:5TDLib10PollO.abstract: Describes one answer option of a poll

Structs/MaskPosition.html#/s:5TDLib12Mas.name: point
Structs/MaskPosition.html#/s:5TDLib12Mas.abstract: Part of the face, relative to which the mask should be placed

Structs/MaskPosition.html#/s:5TDLib12Mas.name: xShift
Structs/MaskPosition.html#/s:5TDLib12Mas.abstract: Shift by X-axis measured in widths of the mask scaled to the face size, from left to right. (For example, -1.0 will place the mask just to the left of the default mask position)

Structs/MaskPosition.html#/s:5TDLib12Mas.name: yShift
Structs/MaskPosition.html#/s:5TDLib12Mas.abstract: Shift by Y-axis measured in heights of the mask scaled to the face size, from top to bottom. (For example, 1.0 will place the mask just below the default mask position)

Structs/MaskPosition.html#/s:5TDLib12Mas.name: scale
Structs/MaskPosition.html#/s:5TDLib12Mas.abstract: Mask scaling coefficient. (For example, 2.0 means a doubled size)

Structs/MaskPosition.html#/s:5TDLib12Mas.name: init(point:xShift:yShift:scale:)
Structs/MaskPosition.html#/s:5TDLib12Mas.abstract: Position on a photo where a mask should be placed

Structs/Minithumbnail.html#/s:5TDLib13Mi.name: init(width:height:data:)
Structs/Minithumbnail.html#/s:5TDLib13Mi.abstract: Thumbnail image of a very poor quality and low resolution

Structs/File.html#/s:5TDLib4FileV12expec.name: expectedSize
Structs/File.html#/s:5TDLib4FileV12expec.abstract: Expected file size in case the exact file size is unknown, but an approximate size is known. Can be used to show download/upload progress

Structs/File.html#/s:5TDLib4FileV5localA.name: local
Structs/File.html#/s:5TDLib4FileV5localA.abstract: Information about the local copy of the file

Structs/File.html#/s:5TDLib4FileV6remote.name: remote
Structs/File.html#/s:5TDLib4FileV6remote.abstract: Information about the remote copy of the file

Structs/RemoteFile.html#/s:5TDLib10Remot.name: id
Structs/RemoteFile.html#/s:5TDLib10Remot.abstract: Remote file identifier; may be empty. Can be used across application restarts or even from other devices for the current user. Uniquely identifies a file, but a file can have a lot of different valid identifiers. -If the ID starts with “http://” or “https://”, it represents the HTTP URL of the file. TDLib is currently unable to download files if only their URL is known. -If downloadFile is called on such a file or if it is sent to a secret chat, TDLib starts a file generation process by sending updateFileGenerationStart to the client with the HTTP URL in the original_path and “#url#” as the conversion string. Clients should generate the file by downloading it to the specified location

Structs/RemoteFile.html#/s:5TDLib10Remot.name: uniqueId
Structs/RemoteFile.html#/s:5TDLib10Remot.abstract: Unique file identifier; may be empty if unknown. The unique file identifier which is the same for the same file even for different users and is persistent over time

Structs/RemoteFile.html#/s:5TDLib10Remot.name: isUploadingActive
Structs/RemoteFile.html#/s:5TDLib10Remot.abstract: True, if the file is currently being uploaded (or a remote copy is being generated by some other means)

Structs/RemoteFile.html#/s:5TDLib10Remot.name: isUploadingCompleted
Structs/RemoteFile.html#/s:5TDLib10Remot.abstract: True, if a remote copy is fully available

Structs/RemoteFile.html#/s:5TDLib10Remot.name: uploadedSize
Structs/RemoteFile.html#/s:5TDLib10Remot.abstract: Size of the remote available part of the file; 0 if unknown

Structs/LocalFile.html#/s:5TDLib9LocalFi.name: path
Structs/LocalFile.html#/s:5TDLib9LocalFi.abstract: Local path to the locally available file part; may be empty

Structs/LocalFile.html#/s:5TDLib9LocalFi.name: canBeDownloaded
Structs/LocalFile.html#/s:5TDLib9LocalFi.abstract: True, if it is possible to try to download or generate the file

Structs/LocalFile.html#/s:5TDLib9LocalFi.name: canBeDeleted
Structs/LocalFile.html#/s:5TDLib9LocalFi.abstract: True, if the file can be deleted

Structs/LocalFile.html#/s:5TDLib9LocalFi.name: isDownloadingActive
Structs/LocalFile.html#/s:5TDLib9LocalFi.abstract: True, if the file is currently being downloaded (or a local copy is being generated by some other means)

Structs/LocalFile.html#/s:5TDLib9LocalFi.name: isDownloadingCompleted
Structs/LocalFile.html#/s:5TDLib9LocalFi.abstract: True, if the local copy is fully available

Structs/LocalFile.html#/s:5TDLib9LocalFi.name: downloadOffset
Structs/LocalFile.html#/s:5TDLib9LocalFi.abstract: Download will be started from this offset. downloaded_prefix_size is calculated from this offset

Structs/LocalFile.html#/s:5TDLib9LocalFi.name: downloadedPrefixSize
Structs/LocalFile.html#/s:5TDLib9LocalFi.abstract: If is_downloading_completed is false, then only some prefix of the file starting from download_offset is ready to be read. downloaded_prefix_size is the size of that prefix

Structs/LocalFile.html#/s:5TDLib9LocalFi.name: downloadedSize
Structs/LocalFile.html#/s:5TDLib9LocalFi.abstract: Total downloaded file bytes. Should be used only for calculating download progress. The actual file size may be bigger, and some parts of it may contain garbage

Structs/TemporaryPasswordState.html#/s:5.name: hasPassword
Structs/TemporaryPasswordState.html#/s:5.abstract: True, if a temporary password is available

Structs/TemporaryPasswordState.html#/s:5.name: validFor
Structs/TemporaryPasswordState.html#/s:5.abstract: Time left before the temporary password expires, in seconds

Structs/TemporaryPasswordState.html#/s:5.name: init(hasPassword:validFor:)
Structs/TemporaryPasswordState.html#/s:5.abstract: Returns information about the availability of a temporary password, which can be used for payments

Structs/RecoveryEmailAddress.html#/s:5TD.name: init(recoveryEmailAddress:)
Structs/RecoveryEmailAddress.html#/s:5TD.abstract: Contains information about the current recovery email address

Structs/PasswordState.html#/s:5TDLib13Pa.name: hasPassword
Structs/PasswordState.html#/s:5TDLib13Pa.abstract: True, if a 2-step verification password is set

Structs/PasswordState.html#/s:5TDLib13Pa.name: passwordHint
Structs/PasswordState.html#/s:5TDLib13Pa.abstract: Hint for the password; may be empty

Structs/PasswordState.html#/s:5TDLib13Pa.name: hasRecoveryEmailAddress
Structs/PasswordState.html#/s:5TDLib13Pa.abstract: True, if a recovery email is set

Structs/PasswordState.html#/s:5TDLib13Pa.name: hasPassportData
Structs/PasswordState.html#/s:5TDLib13Pa.abstract: True, if some Telegram Passport elements were saved

Structs/PasswordState.html#/s:5TDLib13Pa.name: recoveryEmailAddressCodeInfo
Structs/PasswordState.html#/s:5TDLib13Pa.abstract: Information about the recovery email address to which the confirmation email was sent; may be null

Structs/TermsOfService.html#/s:5TDLib14T.name: minUserAge
Structs/TermsOfService.html#/s:5TDLib14T.abstract: The minimum age of a user to be able to accept the terms; 0 if any

Structs/TermsOfService.html#/s:5TDLib14T.name: showPopup
Structs/TermsOfService.html#/s:5TDLib14T.abstract: True, if a blocking popup with terms of service must be shown to the user

Structs/FormattedText.html#/s:5TDLib13Fo.name: entities
Structs/FormattedText.html#/s:5TDLib13Fo.abstract: Entities contained in the text. Entities can be nested, but must not mutually intersect with each other. -Pre, Code and PreCode entities can’t contain other entities. Bold, Italic, Underline and Strikethrough entities can contain and to be contained in all other entities. All other entities can’t contain each other

Structs/TextEntity.html#/s:5TDLib10TextE.name: offset
Structs/TextEntity.html#/s:5TDLib10TextE.abstract: Offset of the entity in UTF-16 code units

Structs/TextEntity.html#/s:5TDLib10TextE.name: length
Structs/TextEntity.html#/s:5TDLib10TextE.abstract: Length of the entity, in UTF-16 code units

Structs/TextEntity.html#/s:5TDLib10TextE.name: init(offset:length:type:)
Structs/TextEntity.html#/s:5TDLib10TextE.abstract: Represents a part of the text that needs to be formatted in some unusual way

Structs/EmailAddressAuthenticationCodeIn.name: emailAddressPattern
Structs/EmailAddressAuthenticationCodeIn.abstract: Pattern of the email address to which an authentication code was sent

Structs/EmailAddressAuthenticationCodeIn.name: init(emailAddressPattern:length:)
Structs/EmailAddressAuthenticationCodeIn.abstract: Information about the email address authentication code that was sent

Structs/AuthenticationCodeInfo.html#/s:5.name: phoneNumber
Structs/AuthenticationCodeInfo.html#/s:5.abstract: A phone number that is being authenticated

Structs/AuthenticationCodeInfo.html#/s:5.name: type
Structs/AuthenticationCodeInfo.html#/s:5.abstract: Describes the way the code was sent to the user

Structs/AuthenticationCodeInfo.html#/s:5.name: nextType
Structs/AuthenticationCodeInfo.html#/s:5.abstract: Describes the way the next code will be sent to the user; may be null

Structs/AuthenticationCodeInfo.html#/s:5.name: timeout
Structs/AuthenticationCodeInfo.html#/s:5.abstract: Timeout before the code should be re-sent, in seconds

Structs/AuthenticationCodeInfo.html#/s:5.name: init(phoneNumber:type:nextType:timeout:)
Structs/AuthenticationCodeInfo.html#/s:5.abstract: Information about the authentication code that was sent

Structs/TdlibParameters.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: useTestDc
Structs/TdlibParameters.html#/s:5TDLib15.abstract: If set to true, the Telegram test environment will be used instead of the production environment

Structs/TdlibParameters.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: databaseDirectory
Structs/TdlibParameters.html#/s:5TDLib15.abstract: The path to the directory for the persistent database; if empty, the current working directory will be used

Structs/TdlibParameters.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: filesDirectory
Structs/TdlibParameters.html#/s:5TDLib15.abstract: The path to the directory for storing files; if empty, database_directory will be used

Structs/TdlibParameters.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: useFileDatabase
Structs/TdlibParameters.html#/s:5TDLib15.abstract: If set to true, information about downloaded and uploaded files will be saved between application restarts

Structs/TdlibParameters.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: useChatInfoDatabase
Structs/TdlibParameters.html#/s:5TDLib15.abstract: If set to true, the library will maintain a cache of users, basic groups, supergroups, channels and secret chats. Implies use_file_database

Structs/TdlibParameters.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: useMessageDatabase
Structs/TdlibParameters.html#/s:5TDLib15.abstract: If set to true, the library will maintain a cache of chats and messages. Implies use_chat_info_database

Structs/TdlibParameters.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: useSecretChats
Structs/TdlibParameters.html#/s:5TDLib15.abstract: If set to true, support for secret chats will be enabled

Structs/TdlibParameters.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: apiId
Structs/TdlibParameters.html#/s:5TDLib15.abstract: Application identifier for Telegram API access, which can be obtained at https://my.telegram.org

Structs/TdlibParameters.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: apiHash
Structs/TdlibParameters.html#/s:5TDLib15.abstract: Application identifier hash for Telegram API access, which can be obtained at https://my.telegram.org

Structs/TdlibParameters.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: systemLanguageCode
Structs/TdlibParameters.html#/s:5TDLib15.abstract: IETF language tag of the user’s operating system language; must be non-empty

Structs/TdlibParameters.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: deviceModel
Structs/TdlibParameters.html#/s:5TDLib15.abstract: Model of the device the application is being run on; must be non-empty

Structs/TdlibParameters.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: systemVersion
Structs/TdlibParameters.html#/s:5TDLib15.abstract: Version of the operating system the application is being run on; must be non-empty

Structs/TdlibParameters.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: enableStorageOptimizer
Structs/TdlibParameters.html#/s:5TDLib15.abstract: If set to true, old files will automatically be deleted

Structs/TdlibParameters.html#/s:5TDLib15.name: ignoreFileNames
Structs/TdlibParameters.html#/s:5TDLib15.abstract: If set to true, original file names will be ignored. Otherwise, downloaded files will be saved under names as close as possible to the original name

Structs/Ok.html#/s:5TDLib2OkVACycfc.name: init()
Structs/Ok.html#/s:5TDLib2OkVACycfc.abstract: An object of this type is returned on a successful function call for certain functions

Structs/Error.html#/s:5TDLib5ErrorV4code.name: code
Structs/Error.html#/s:5TDLib5ErrorV4code.abstract: Error code; subject to future changes. If the error code is 406, the error message must not be processed in any way and must not be displayed to the user

Structs/Error.html#/s:5TDLib5ErrorV4code.name: init(code:message:)
Structs/Error.html#/s:5TDLib5ErrorV4code.abstract: An object of this type can be returned on every function call, in case of an error

Structs/Error.html.name: Error
Structs/Error.html.abstract: An object of this type can be returned on every function call, in case of an error

Structs/Ok.html.name: Ok
Structs/Ok.html.abstract: An object of this type is returned on a successful function call for certain functions

Structs/AuthenticationCodeInfo.html.name: AuthenticationCodeInfo
Structs/AuthenticationCodeInfo.html.abstract: Information about the authentication code that was sent

Structs/EmailAddressAuthenticationCodeIn.name: EmailAddressAuthenticationCodeInfo
Structs/EmailAddressAuthenticationCodeIn.abstract: Information about the email address authentication code that was sent

Structs/TextEntity.html.name: TextEntity
Structs/TextEntity.html.abstract: Represents a part of the text that needs to be formatted in some unusual way

Structs/RecoveryEmailAddress.html.name: RecoveryEmailAddress
Structs/RecoveryEmailAddress.html.abstract: Contains information about the current recovery email address

Structs/TemporaryPasswordState.html.name: TemporaryPasswordState
Structs/TemporaryPasswordState.html.abstract: Returns information about the availability of a temporary password, which can be used for payments

Structs/Minithumbnail.html.name: Minithumbnail
Structs/Minithumbnail.html.abstract: Thumbnail image of a very poor quality and low resolution

Structs/MaskPosition.html.name: MaskPosition
Structs/MaskPosition.html.abstract: Position on a photo where a mask should be placed

Structs/PollOption.html.name: PollOption
Structs/PollOption.html.abstract: Describes one answer option of a poll

Structs/Animation.html.name: Animation
Structs/Animation.html.abstract: Describes an animation file. The animation must be encoded in GIF or MPEG4 format

Structs/Audio.html.name: Audio
Structs/Audio.html.abstract: Describes an audio file. Audio is usually in MP3 or M4A format

Structs/VideoNote.html.name: VideoNote
Structs/VideoNote.html.abstract: Describes a video note. The video must be equal in width and height, cropped to a circle, and stored in MPEG4 format

Structs/VoiceNote.html.name: VoiceNote
Structs/VoiceNote.html.abstract: Describes a voice note. The voice note must be encoded with the Opus codec, and stored inside an OGG container. Voice notes can have only a single audio channel

Structs/BotInfo.html.name: BotInfo
Structs/BotInfo.html.abstract: Provides information about a bot and its supported commands

Structs/ChatLocation.html.name: ChatLocation
Structs/ChatLocation.html.abstract: Represents a location to which a chat is connected

Structs/UserFullInfo.html.name: UserFullInfo
Structs/UserFullInfo.html.abstract: Contains full information about a user (except the full list of profile photos)

Structs/UserProfilePhoto.html.name: UserProfilePhoto
Structs/UserProfilePhoto.html.abstract: Contains full information about a user profile photo

Structs/UserProfilePhotos.html.name: UserProfilePhotos
Structs/UserProfilePhotos.html.abstract: Contains part of the list of user photos

Structs/ChatPermissions.html.name: ChatPermissions
Structs/ChatPermissions.html.abstract: Describes actions that a user is allowed to take in a chat

Structs/ChatMember.html.name: ChatMember
Structs/ChatMember.html.abstract: A user with information about joining/leaving a chat

Structs/BasicGroup.html.name: BasicGroup
Structs/BasicGroup.html.abstract: Represents a basic group of 0-200 users (must be upgraded to a supergroup to accommodate more than 200 users)

Structs/BasicGroupFullInfo.html.name: BasicGroupFullInfo
Structs/BasicGroupFullInfo.html.abstract: Contains full information about a basic group

Structs/Supergroup.html.name: Supergroup
Structs/Supergroup.html.abstract: Represents a supergroup or channel with zero or more members (subscribers in the case of channels). From the point of view of the system, a channel is a special kind of a supergroup: only administrators can post and see the list of members, and posts from all administrators use the name and photo of the channel instead of individual names and profile photos. Unlike supergroups, channels can have an unlimited number of subscribers

Structs/SupergroupFullInfo.html.name: SupergroupFullInfo
Structs/SupergroupFullInfo.html.abstract: Contains full information about a supergroup or channel

Structs/FoundMessages.html.name: FoundMessages
Structs/FoundMessages.html.abstract: Contains a list of messages found by a search

Structs/ChatNotificationSettings.html.name: ChatNotificationSettings
Structs/ChatNotificationSettings.html.abstract: Contains information about notification settings for a chat

Structs/ScopeNotificationSettings.html.name: ScopeNotificationSettings
Structs/ScopeNotificationSettings.html.abstract: Contains information about notification settings for several chats

Structs/Chat.html.name: Chat
Structs/Chat.html.abstract: A chat. (Can be a private chat, basic group, supergroup, or secret chat)

Structs/ChatsNearby.html.name: ChatsNearby
Structs/ChatsNearby.html.abstract: Represents a list of chats located nearby

Structs/ChatInviteLinkInfo.html.name: ChatInviteLinkInfo
Structs/ChatInviteLinkInfo.html.abstract: Contains information about a chat invite link

Structs/KeyboardButton.html.name: KeyboardButton
Structs/KeyboardButton.html.abstract: Represents a single button in a bot keyboard

Structs/InlineKeyboardButton.html.name: InlineKeyboardButton
Structs/InlineKeyboardButton.html.abstract: Represents a single button in an inline keyboard

Structs/PageBlockCaption.html.name: PageBlockCaption
Structs/PageBlockCaption.html.abstract: Contains a caption of an instant view web page block, consisting of a text and a trailing credit

Structs/PageBlockListItem.html.name: PageBlockListItem
Structs/PageBlockListItem.html.abstract: Describes an item of a list page block

Structs/WebPageInstantView.html.name: WebPageInstantView
Structs/WebPageInstantView.html.abstract: Describes an instant view page for a web page

Structs/LabeledPricePart.html.name: LabeledPricePart
Structs/LabeledPricePart.html.abstract: Portion of the price of a product (e.g., “delivery cost”, “tax amount”)

Structs/PaymentForm.html.name: PaymentForm
Structs/PaymentForm.html.abstract: Contains information about an invoice payment form

Structs/ValidatedOrderInfo.html.name: ValidatedOrderInfo
Structs/ValidatedOrderInfo.html.abstract: Contains a temporary identifier of validated order information, which is stored for one hour. Also contains the available shipping options

Structs/PaymentResult.html.name: PaymentResult
Structs/PaymentResult.html.abstract: Contains the result of a payment request

Structs/DatedFile.html.name: DatedFile
Structs/DatedFile.html.abstract: File with the date it was uploaded

Structs/Date.html.name: Date
Structs/Date.html.abstract: Represents a date according to the Gregorian calendar

Structs/InputIdentityDocument.html.name: InputIdentityDocument
Structs/InputIdentityDocument.html.abstract: An identity document to be saved to Telegram Passport

Structs/PersonalDocument.html.name: PersonalDocument
Structs/PersonalDocument.html.abstract: A personal document, containing some information about a user

Structs/InputPersonalDocument.html.name: InputPersonalDocument
Structs/InputPersonalDocument.html.abstract: A personal document to be saved to Telegram Passport

Structs/PassportElements.html.name: PassportElements
Structs/PassportElements.html.abstract: Contains information about saved Telegram Passport elements

Structs/PassportElementError.html.name: PassportElementError
Structs/PassportElementError.html.abstract: Contains the description of an error in a Telegram Passport element

Structs/PassportSuitableElement.html.name: PassportSuitableElement
Structs/PassportSuitableElement.html.abstract: Contains information about a Telegram Passport element that was requested by a service

Structs/PassportRequiredElement.html.name: PassportRequiredElement
Structs/PassportRequiredElement.html.abstract: Contains a description of the required Telegram Passport element that was requested by a service

Structs/PassportAuthorizationForm.html.name: PassportAuthorizationForm
Structs/PassportAuthorizationForm.html.abstract: Contains information about a Telegram Passport authorization form that was requested

Structs/PassportElementsWithErrors.html.name: PassportElementsWithErrors
Structs/PassportElementsWithErrors.html.abstract: Contains information about a Telegram Passport elements and corresponding errors

Structs/EncryptedPassportElement.html.name: EncryptedPassportElement
Structs/EncryptedPassportElement.html.abstract: Contains information about an encrypted Telegram Passport element; for bots only

Structs/InputPassportElementError.html.name: InputPassportElementError
Structs/InputPassportElementError.html.abstract: Contains the description of an error in a Telegram Passport element; for bots only

Structs/InputThumbnail.html.name: InputThumbnail
Structs/InputThumbnail.html.abstract: A thumbnail to be sent along with a file; should be in JPEG or WEBP format for stickers, and less than 200 kB in size

Structs/SendMessageOptions.html.name: SendMessageOptions
Structs/SendMessageOptions.html.abstract: Options to be used when a message is send

Structs/StickerSetInfo.html.name: StickerSetInfo
Structs/StickerSetInfo.html.abstract: Represents short information about a sticker set

Structs/PhoneNumberAuthenticationSetting.name: PhoneNumberAuthenticationSettings
Structs/PhoneNumberAuthenticationSetting.abstract: Contains settings for the authentication of the user’s phone number

Structs/ImportedContacts.html.name: ImportedContacts
Structs/ImportedContacts.html.abstract: Represents the result of an ImportContacts request

Structs/InlineQueryResults.html.name: InlineQueryResults
Structs/InlineQueryResults.html.abstract: Represents the results of the inline query. Use sendInlineQueryResultMessage to send the result of the query

Structs/CallbackQueryAnswer.html.name: CallbackQueryAnswer
Structs/CallbackQueryAnswer.html.abstract: Contains a bot’s answer to a callback query

Structs/CustomRequestResult.html.name: CustomRequestResult
Structs/CustomRequestResult.html.abstract: Contains the result of a custom request

Structs/GameHighScore.html.name: GameHighScore
Structs/GameHighScore.html.abstract: Contains one row of the game high score table

Structs/GameHighScores.html.name: GameHighScores
Structs/GameHighScores.html.abstract: Contains a list of game high scores

Structs/ChatEventLogFilters.html.name: ChatEventLogFilters
Structs/ChatEventLogFilters.html.abstract: Represents a set of filters used to obtain a chat event log

Structs/LanguagePackStrings.html.name: LanguagePackStrings
Structs/LanguagePackStrings.html.abstract: Contains a list of language pack strings

Structs/LocalizationTargetInfo.html.name: LocalizationTargetInfo
Structs/LocalizationTargetInfo.html.abstract: Contains information about the current localization target

Structs/PushReceiverId.html.name: PushReceiverId
Structs/PushReceiverId.html.abstract: Contains a globally unique push receiver identifier, which can be used to identify which account has received a push notification

Structs/JsonObjectMember.html.name: JsonObjectMember
Structs/JsonObjectMember.html.abstract: Represents one member of a JSON object

Structs/UserPrivacySettingRules.html.name: UserPrivacySettingRules
Structs/UserPrivacySettingRules.html.abstract: A list of privacy rules. Rules are matched in the specified order. The first matched rule defines the privacy setting for a given user. If no rule matches, the action is not allowed

Structs/AccountTtl.html.name: AccountTtl
Structs/AccountTtl.html.abstract: Contains information about the period of inactivity after which the current user’s account will automatically be deleted

Structs/Session.html.name: Session
Structs/Session.html.abstract: Contains information about one session in a Telegram application used by the current user. Sessions should be shown to the user in the returned order

Structs/ConnectedWebsite.html.name: ConnectedWebsite
Structs/ConnectedWebsite.html.abstract: Contains information about one website the current user is logged in with Telegram

Structs/ConnectedWebsites.html.name: ConnectedWebsites
Structs/ConnectedWebsites.html.abstract: Contains a list of websites the current user is logged in with Telegram

Structs/PublicMessageLink.html.name: PublicMessageLink
Structs/PublicMessageLink.html.abstract: Contains a public HTTPS link to a message in a supergroup or channel with a username

Structs/MessageLinkInfo.html.name: MessageLinkInfo
Structs/MessageLinkInfo.html.abstract: Contains information about a link to a message in a chat

Structs/StorageStatisticsByFileType.html.name: StorageStatisticsByFileType
Structs/StorageStatisticsByFileType.html.abstract: Contains the storage usage statistics for a specific file type

Structs/StorageStatisticsByChat.html.name: StorageStatisticsByChat
Structs/StorageStatisticsByChat.html.abstract: Contains the storage usage statistics for a specific chat

Structs/StorageStatistics.html.name: StorageStatistics
Structs/StorageStatistics.html.abstract: Contains the exact storage usage statistics split by chats and file type

Structs/StorageStatisticsFast.html.name: StorageStatisticsFast
Structs/StorageStatisticsFast.html.abstract: Contains approximate storage usage statistics, excluding files of unknown file type

Structs/NetworkStatistics.html.name: NetworkStatistics
Structs/NetworkStatistics.html.abstract: A full list of available network statistic entries

Structs/AutoDownloadSettingsPresets.html.name: AutoDownloadSettingsPresets
Structs/AutoDownloadSettingsPresets.html.abstract: Contains auto-download settings presets for the user

Structs/TMeUrl.html.name: TMeUrl
Structs/TMeUrl.html.abstract: Represents a URL linking to an internal Telegram entity

Structs/Seconds.html.name: Seconds
Structs/Seconds.html.abstract: Contains a value representing a number of seconds

Structs/DeepLinkInfo.html.name: DeepLinkInfo
Structs/DeepLinkInfo.html.abstract: Contains information about a tg:// deep link

Structs/InputSticker.html.name: InputSticker
Structs/InputSticker.html.abstract: Describes a sticker that should be added to a sticker set

Structs/LogVerbosityLevel.html.name: LogVerbosityLevel
Structs/LogVerbosityLevel.html.abstract: Contains a TDLib internal log verbosity level

Structs/LogTags.html.name: LogTags
Structs/LogTags.html.abstract: Contains a list of available TDLib internal log tags

Structs/TestInt.html.name: TestInt
Structs/TestInt.html.abstract: A simple object containing a number; for testing only

Structs/TestString.html.name: TestString
Structs/TestString.html.abstract: A simple object containing a string; for testing only

Structs/TestBytes.html.name: TestBytes
Structs/TestBytes.html.abstract: A simple object containing a sequence of bytes; for testing only

Structs/TestVectorInt.html.name: TestVectorInt
Structs/TestVectorInt.html.abstract: A simple object containing a vector of numbers; for testing only

Structs/TestVectorIntObject.html.name: TestVectorIntObject
Structs/TestVectorIntObject.html.abstract: A simple object containing a vector of objects that hold a number; for testing only

Structs/TestVectorString.html.name: TestVectorString
Structs/TestVectorString.html.abstract: A simple object containing a vector of strings; for testing only

Structs/TestVectorStringObject.html.name: TestVectorStringObject
Structs/TestVectorStringObject.html.abstract: A simple object containing a vector of objects that hold a string; for testing only

Structs/GetAuthorizationState.html.name: GetAuthorizationState
Structs/GetAuthorizationState.html.abstract: Returns the current authorization state; this is an offline request. For informational purposes only. Use updateAuthorizationState instead to maintain the current authorization state

Structs/SetTdlibParameters.html.name: SetTdlibParameters
Structs/SetTdlibParameters.html.abstract: Sets the parameters for TDLib initialization. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitTdlibParameters

Structs/CheckDatabaseEncryptionKey.html.name: CheckDatabaseEncryptionKey
Structs/CheckDatabaseEncryptionKey.html.abstract: Checks the database encryption key for correctness. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitEncryptionKey

Structs/SetAuthenticationPhoneNumber.htm.name: SetAuthenticationPhoneNumber
Structs/SetAuthenticationPhoneNumber.htm.abstract: Sets the phone number of the user and sends an authentication code to the user. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitPhoneNumber, -or if there is no pending authentication query and the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitCode, authorizationStateWaitRegistration, or authorizationStateWaitPassword

Structs/ResendAuthenticationCode.html.name: ResendAuthenticationCode
Structs/ResendAuthenticationCode.html.abstract: Re-sends an authentication code to the user. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitCode and the next_code_type of the result is not null

Structs/CheckAuthenticationCode.html.name: CheckAuthenticationCode
Structs/CheckAuthenticationCode.html.abstract: Checks the authentication code. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitCode

Structs/RequestQrCodeAuthentication.html.name: RequestQrCodeAuthentication
Structs/RequestQrCodeAuthentication.html.abstract: Requests QR code authentication by scanning a QR code on another logged in device. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitPhoneNumber

Structs/RegisterUser.html.name: RegisterUser
Structs/RegisterUser.html.abstract: Finishes user registration. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitRegistration

Structs/CheckAuthenticationPassword.html.name: CheckAuthenticationPassword
Structs/CheckAuthenticationPassword.html.abstract: Checks the authentication password for correctness. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitPassword

Structs/RequestAuthenticationPasswordRec.name: RequestAuthenticationPasswordRecovery
Structs/RequestAuthenticationPasswordRec.abstract: Requests to send a password recovery code to an email address that was previously set up. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitPassword

Structs/RecoverAuthenticationPassword.ht.name: RecoverAuthenticationPassword
Structs/RecoverAuthenticationPassword.ht.abstract: Recovers the password with a password recovery code sent to an email address that was previously set up. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitPassword

Structs/CheckAuthenticationBotToken.html.name: CheckAuthenticationBotToken
Structs/CheckAuthenticationBotToken.html.abstract: Checks the authentication token of a bot; to log in as a bot. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitPhoneNumber. Can be used instead of setAuthenticationPhoneNumber and checkAuthenticationCode to log in

Structs/LogOut.html.name: LogOut
Structs/LogOut.html.abstract: Closes the TDLib instance after a proper logout. Requires an available network connection. All local data will be destroyed. After the logout completes, updateAuthorizationState with authorizationStateClosed will be sent

Structs/Close.html.name: Close
Structs/Close.html.abstract: Closes the TDLib instance. All databases will be flushed to disk and properly closed. After the close completes, updateAuthorizationState with authorizationStateClosed will be sent

Structs/Destroy.html.name: Destroy
Structs/Destroy.html.abstract: Closes the TDLib instance, destroying all local data without a proper logout. The current user session will remain in the list of all active sessions. All local data will be destroyed. After the destruction completes updateAuthorizationState with authorizationStateClosed will be sent

Structs/ConfirmQrCodeAuthentication.html.name: ConfirmQrCodeAuthentication
Structs/ConfirmQrCodeAuthentication.html.abstract: Confirms QR code authentication on another device. Returns created session on success

Structs/GetCurrentState.html.name: GetCurrentState
Structs/GetCurrentState.html.abstract: Returns all updates needed to restore current TDLib state, i.e. all actual UpdateAuthorizationState/UpdateUser/UpdateNewChat and others. This is especially useful if TDLib is run in a separate process. This is an offline method. Can be called before authorization

Structs/SetDatabaseEncryptionKey.html.name: SetDatabaseEncryptionKey
Structs/SetDatabaseEncryptionKey.html.abstract: Changes the database encryption key. Usually the encryption key is never changed and is stored in some OS keychain

Structs/SetPassword.html.name: SetPassword
Structs/SetPassword.html.abstract: Changes the password for the user. If a new recovery email address is specified, then the change will not be applied until the new recovery email address is confirmed

Structs/GetRecoveryEmailAddress.html.name: GetRecoveryEmailAddress
Structs/GetRecoveryEmailAddress.html.abstract: Returns a 2-step verification recovery email address that was previously set up. This method can be used to verify a password provided by the user

Structs/SetRecoveryEmailAddress.html.name: SetRecoveryEmailAddress
Structs/SetRecoveryEmailAddress.html.abstract: Changes the 2-step verification recovery email address of the user. If a new recovery email address is specified, then the change will not be applied until the new recovery email address is confirmed. -If new_recovery_email_address is the same as the email address that is currently set up, this call succeeds immediately and aborts all other requests waiting for an email confirmation

Structs/CheckRecoveryEmailAddressCode.ht.name: CheckRecoveryEmailAddressCode
Structs/CheckRecoveryEmailAddressCode.ht.abstract: Checks the 2-step verification recovery email address verification code

Structs/ResendRecoveryEmailAddressCode.h.name: ResendRecoveryEmailAddressCode
Structs/ResendRecoveryEmailAddressCode.h.abstract: Resends the 2-step verification recovery email address verification code

Structs/RequestPasswordRecovery.html.name: RequestPasswordRecovery
Structs/RequestPasswordRecovery.html.abstract: Requests to send a password recovery code to an email address that was previously set up

Structs/RecoverPassword.html.name: RecoverPassword
Structs/RecoverPassword.html.abstract: Recovers the password using a recovery code sent to an email address that was previously set up

Structs/CreateTemporaryPassword.html.name: CreateTemporaryPassword
Structs/CreateTemporaryPassword.html.abstract: Creates a new temporary password for processing payments

Structs/GetTemporaryPasswordState.html.name: GetTemporaryPasswordState
Structs/GetTemporaryPasswordState.html.abstract: Returns information about the current temporary password

Structs/GetUser.html.name: GetUser
Structs/GetUser.html.abstract: Returns information about a user by their identifier. This is an offline request if the current user is not a bot

Structs/GetUserFullInfo.html.name: GetUserFullInfo
Structs/GetUserFullInfo.html.abstract: Returns full information about a user by their identifier

Structs/GetBasicGroup.html.name: GetBasicGroup
Structs/GetBasicGroup.html.abstract: Returns information about a basic group by its identifier. This is an offline request if the current user is not a bot

Structs/GetBasicGroupFullInfo.html.name: GetBasicGroupFullInfo
Structs/GetBasicGroupFullInfo.html.abstract: Returns full information about a basic group by its identifier

Structs/GetSupergroup.html.name: GetSupergroup
Structs/GetSupergroup.html.abstract: Returns information about a supergroup or a channel by its identifier. This is an offline request if the current user is not a bot

Structs/GetSupergroupFullInfo.html.name: GetSupergroupFullInfo
Structs/GetSupergroupFullInfo.html.abstract: Returns full information about a supergroup or a channel by its identifier, cached for up to 1 minute

Structs/GetSecretChat.html.name: GetSecretChat
Structs/GetSecretChat.html.abstract: Returns information about a secret chat by its identifier. This is an offline request

Structs/GetChat.html.name: GetChat
Structs/GetChat.html.abstract: Returns information about a chat by its identifier, this is an offline request if the current user is not a bot

Structs/GetMessageLocally.html.name: GetMessageLocally
Structs/GetMessageLocally.html.abstract: Returns information about a message, if it is available locally without sending network request. This is an offline request

Structs/GetRepliedMessage.html.name: GetRepliedMessage
Structs/GetRepliedMessage.html.abstract: Returns information about a message that is replied by given message

Structs/GetChatPinnedMessage.html.name: GetChatPinnedMessage
Structs/GetChatPinnedMessage.html.abstract: Returns information about a pinned chat message

Structs/GetMessages.html.name: GetMessages
Structs/GetMessages.html.abstract: Returns information about messages. If a message is not found, returns null on the corresponding position of the result

Structs/GetFile.html.name: GetFile
Structs/GetFile.html.abstract: Returns information about a file; this is an offline request

Structs/GetRemoteFile.html.name: GetRemoteFile
Structs/GetRemoteFile.html.abstract: Returns information about a file by its remote ID; this is an offline request. Can be used to register a URL as a file for further uploading, or sending as a message. Even the request succeeds, the file can be used only if it is still accessible to the user. -For example, if the file is from a message, then the message must be not deleted and accessible to the user. If the file database is disabled, then the corresponding object with the file must be preloaded by the client

Structs/GetChats.html.name: GetChats
Structs/GetChats.html.abstract: Returns an ordered list of chats in a chat list. Chats are sorted by the pair (order, chat_id) in decreasing order. (For example, to get a list of chats from the beginning, the offset_order should be equal to a biggest signed 64-bit number 9223372036854775807 == 2^63 - 1). -For optimal performance the number of returned chats is chosen by the library

Structs/SearchPublicChat.html.name: SearchPublicChat
Structs/SearchPublicChat.html.abstract: Searches a public chat by its username. Currently only private chats, supergroups and channels can be public. Returns the chat if found; otherwise an error is returned

Structs/SearchPublicChats.html.name: SearchPublicChats
Structs/SearchPublicChats.html.abstract: Searches public chats by looking for specified query in their username and title. Currently only private chats, supergroups and channels can be public. Returns a meaningful number of results. Returns nothing if the length of the searched username prefix is less than 5. Excludes private chats with contacts and chats from the chat list from the results

Structs/SearchChats.html.name: SearchChats
Structs/SearchChats.html.abstract: Searches for the specified query in the title and username of already known chats, this is an offline request. Returns chats in the order seen in the chat list

Structs/SearchChatsOnServer.html.name: SearchChatsOnServer
Structs/SearchChatsOnServer.html.abstract: Searches for the specified query in the title and username of already known chats via request to the server. Returns chats in the order seen in the chat list

Structs/SearchChatsNearby.html.name: SearchChatsNearby
Structs/SearchChatsNearby.html.abstract: Returns a list of users and location-based supergroups nearby. The list of users nearby will be updated for 60 seconds after the request by the updates updateUsersNearby. The request should be sent again every 25 seconds with adjusted location to not miss new chats

Structs/GetTopChats.html.name: GetTopChats
Structs/GetTopChats.html.abstract: Returns a list of frequently used chats. Supported only if the chat info database is enabled

Structs/RemoveTopChat.html.name: RemoveTopChat
Structs/RemoveTopChat.html.abstract: Removes a chat from the list of frequently used chats. Supported only if the chat info database is enabled

Structs/AddRecentlyFoundChat.html.name: AddRecentlyFoundChat
Structs/AddRecentlyFoundChat.html.abstract: Adds a chat to the list of recently found chats. The chat is added to the beginning of the list. If the chat is already in the list, it will be removed from the list first

Structs/RemoveRecentlyFoundChat.html.name: RemoveRecentlyFoundChat
Structs/RemoveRecentlyFoundChat.html.abstract: Removes a chat from the list of recently found chats

Structs/ClearRecentlyFoundChats.html.name: ClearRecentlyFoundChats
Structs/ClearRecentlyFoundChats.html.abstract: Clears the list of recently found chats

Structs/CheckChatUsername.html.name: CheckChatUsername
Structs/CheckChatUsername.html.abstract: Checks whether a username can be set for a chat

Structs/GetCreatedPublicChats.html.name: GetCreatedPublicChats
Structs/GetCreatedPublicChats.html.abstract: Returns a list of public chats of the specified type, owned by the user

Structs/CheckCreatedPublicChatsLimit.htm.name: CheckCreatedPublicChatsLimit
Structs/CheckCreatedPublicChatsLimit.htm.abstract: Checks whether the maximum number of owned public chats has been reached. Returns corresponding error if the limit was reached

Structs/GetSuitableDiscussionChats.html.name: GetSuitableDiscussionChats
Structs/GetSuitableDiscussionChats.html.abstract: Returns a list of basic group and supergroup chats, which can be used as a discussion group for a channel. Basic group chats need to be first upgraded to supergroups before they can be set as a discussion group

Structs/GetInactiveSupergroupChats.html.name: GetInactiveSupergroupChats
Structs/GetInactiveSupergroupChats.html.abstract: Returns a list of recently inactive supergroups and channels. Can be used when user reaches limit on the number of joined supergroups and channels and receives CHANNELS_TOO_MUCH error

Structs/GetGroupsInCommon.html.name: GetGroupsInCommon
