Structs/GetGroupsInCommon.html.abstract: Returns a list of common group chats with a given user. Chats are sorted by their type and creation date

Structs/GetChatHistory.html.name: GetChatHistory
Structs/GetChatHistory.html.abstract: Returns messages in a chat. The messages are returned in a reverse chronological order (i.e., in order of decreasing message_id). -For optimal performance the number of returned messages is chosen by the library. This is an offline request if only_local is true

Structs/DeleteChatHistory.html.name: DeleteChatHistory
Structs/DeleteChatHistory.html.abstract: Deletes all messages in the chat. Use Chat.can_be_deleted_only_for_self and Chat.can_be_deleted_for_all_users fields to find whether and how the method can be applied to the chat

Structs/SearchChatMessages.html.name: SearchChatMessages
Structs/SearchChatMessages.html.abstract: Searches for messages with given words in the chat. Returns the results in reverse chronological order, i.e. in order of decreasing message_id. Cannot be used in secret chats with a non-empty query -(searchSecretMessages should be used instead), or without an enabled message database. For optimal performance the number of returned messages is chosen by the library

Structs/SearchMessages.html.name: SearchMessages
Structs/SearchMessages.html.abstract: Searches for messages in all chats except secret chats. Returns the results in reverse chronological order (i.e., in order of decreasing (date, chat_id, message_id)). -For optimal performance the number of returned messages is chosen by the library

Structs/SearchSecretMessages.html.name: SearchSecretMessages
Structs/SearchSecretMessages.html.abstract: Searches for messages in secret chats. Returns the results in reverse chronological order. For optimal performance the number of returned messages is chosen by the library

Structs/SearchCallMessages.html.name: SearchCallMessages
Structs/SearchCallMessages.html.abstract: Searches for call messages. Returns the results in reverse chronological order (i. e., in order of decreasing message_id). For optimal performance the number of returned messages is chosen by the library

Structs/SearchChatRecentLocationMessages.name: SearchChatRecentLocationMessages
Structs/SearchChatRecentLocationMessages.abstract: Returns information about the recent locations of chat members that were sent to the chat. Returns up to 1 location message per user

Structs/GetActiveLiveLocationMessages.ht.name: GetActiveLiveLocationMessages
Structs/GetActiveLiveLocationMessages.ht.abstract: Returns all active live locations that should be updated by the client. The list is persistent across application restarts only if the message database is used

Structs/GetChatMessageByDate.html.name: GetChatMessageByDate
Structs/GetChatMessageByDate.html.abstract: Returns the last message sent in a chat no later than the specified date

Structs/GetChatMessageCount.html.name: GetChatMessageCount
Structs/GetChatMessageCount.html.abstract: Returns approximate number of messages of the specified type in the chat

Structs/GetChatScheduledMessages.html.name: GetChatScheduledMessages
Structs/GetChatScheduledMessages.html.abstract: Returns all scheduled messages in a chat. The messages are returned in a reverse chronological order (i.e., in order of decreasing message_id)

Structs/RemoveNotification.html.name: RemoveNotification
Structs/RemoveNotification.html.abstract: Removes an active notification from notification list. Needs to be called only if the notification is removed by the current user

Structs/RemoveNotificationGroup.html.name: RemoveNotificationGroup
Structs/RemoveNotificationGroup.html.abstract: Removes a group of active notifications. Needs to be called only if the notification group is removed by the current user

Structs/GetPublicMessageLink.html.name: GetPublicMessageLink
Structs/GetPublicMessageLink.html.abstract: Returns a public HTTPS link to a message. Available only for messages in supergroups and channels with a username

Structs/GetMessageLink.html.name: GetMessageLink
Structs/GetMessageLink.html.abstract: Returns a private HTTPS link to a message in a chat. Available only for already sent messages in supergroups and channels. The link will work only for members of the chat

Structs/GetMessageLinkInfo.html.name: GetMessageLinkInfo
Structs/GetMessageLinkInfo.html.abstract: Returns information about a public or private message link

Structs/SendMessage.html.name: SendMessage
Structs/SendMessage.html.abstract: Sends a message. Returns the sent message

Structs/SendMessageAlbum.html.name: SendMessageAlbum
Structs/SendMessageAlbum.html.abstract: Sends messages grouped together into an album. Currently only photo and video messages can be grouped into an album. Returns sent messages

Structs/SendBotStartMessage.html.name: SendBotStartMessage
Structs/SendBotStartMessage.html.abstract: Invites a bot to a chat (if it is not yet a member) and sends it the /start command. Bots can’t be invited to a private chat other than the chat with the bot. Bots can’t be invited to channels (although they can be added as admins) and secret chats. Returns the sent message

Structs/SendInlineQueryResultMessage.htm.name: SendInlineQueryResultMessage
Structs/SendInlineQueryResultMessage.htm.abstract: Sends the result of an inline query as a message. Returns the sent message. Always clears a chat draft message

Structs/ForwardMessages.html.name: ForwardMessages
Structs/ForwardMessages.html.abstract: Forwards previously sent messages. Returns the forwarded messages in the same order as the message identifiers passed in message_ids. If a message can’t be forwarded, null will be returned instead of the message

Structs/ResendMessages.html.name: ResendMessages
Structs/ResendMessages.html.abstract: Resends messages which failed to send. Can be called only for messages for which messageSendingStateFailed.can_retry is true and after specified in messageSendingStateFailed.retry_after time passed. -If a message is re-sent, the corresponding failed to send message is deleted. Returns the sent messages in the same order as the message identifiers passed in message_ids. If a message can’t be re-sent, null will be returned instead of the message

Structs/SendChatSetTtlMessage.html.name: SendChatSetTtlMessage
Structs/SendChatSetTtlMessage.html.abstract: Changes the current TTL setting (sets a new self-destruct timer) in a secret chat and sends the corresponding message

Structs/SendChatScreenshotTakenNotificat.name: SendChatScreenshotTakenNotification
Structs/SendChatScreenshotTakenNotificat.abstract: Sends a notification about a screenshot taken in a chat. Supported only in private and secret chats

Structs/AddLocalMessage.html.name: AddLocalMessage
Structs/AddLocalMessage.html.abstract: Adds a local message to a chat. The message is persistent across application restarts only if the message database is used. Returns the added message

Structs/DeleteChatMessagesFromUser.html.name: DeleteChatMessagesFromUser
Structs/DeleteChatMessagesFromUser.html.abstract: Deletes all messages sent by the specified user to a chat. Supported only for supergroups; requires can_delete_messages administrator privileges

Structs/EditMessageText.html.name: EditMessageText
Structs/EditMessageText.html.abstract: Edits the text of a message (or a text of a game message). Returns the edited message after the edit is completed on the server side

Structs/EditMessageLiveLocation.html.name: EditMessageLiveLocation
Structs/EditMessageLiveLocation.html.abstract: Edits the message content of a live location. Messages can be edited for a limited period of time specified in the live location. Returns the edited message after the edit is completed on the server side

Structs/EditMessageMedia.html.name: EditMessageMedia
Structs/EditMessageMedia.html.abstract: Edits the content of a message with an animation, an audio, a document, a photo or a video. The media in the message can’t be replaced if the message was set to self-destruct. Media can’t be replaced by self-destructing media. Media in an album can be edited only to contain a photo or a video. Returns the edited message after the edit is completed on the server side

Structs/EditMessageCaption.html.name: EditMessageCaption
Structs/EditMessageCaption.html.abstract: Edits the message content caption. Returns the edited message after the edit is completed on the server side

Structs/EditMessageReplyMarkup.html.name: EditMessageReplyMarkup
Structs/EditMessageReplyMarkup.html.abstract: Edits the message reply markup; for bots only. Returns the edited message after the edit is completed on the server side

Structs/EditInlineMessageText.html.name: EditInlineMessageText
Structs/EditInlineMessageText.html.abstract: Edits the text of an inline text or game message sent via a bot; for bots only

Structs/EditInlineMessageLiveLocation.ht.name: EditInlineMessageLiveLocation
Structs/EditInlineMessageLiveLocation.ht.abstract: Edits the content of a live location in an inline message sent via a bot; for bots only

Structs/EditInlineMessageMedia.html.name: EditInlineMessageMedia
Structs/EditInlineMessageMedia.html.abstract: Edits the content of a message with an animation, an audio, a document, a photo or a video in an inline message sent via a bot; for bots only

Structs/EditInlineMessageCaption.html.name: EditInlineMessageCaption
Structs/EditInlineMessageCaption.html.abstract: Edits the caption of an inline message sent via a bot; for bots only

Structs/EditInlineMessageReplyMarkup.htm.name: EditInlineMessageReplyMarkup
Structs/EditInlineMessageReplyMarkup.htm.abstract: Edits the reply markup of an inline message sent via a bot; for bots only

Structs/EditMessageSchedulingState.html.name: EditMessageSchedulingState
Structs/EditMessageSchedulingState.html.abstract: Edits the time when a scheduled message will be sent. Scheduling state of all messages in the same album or forwarded together with the message will be also changed

Structs/GetTextEntities.html.name: GetTextEntities
Structs/GetTextEntities.html.abstract: Returns all entities (mentions, hashtags, cashtags, bot commands, URLs, and email addresses) contained in the text. This is an offline method. Can be called before authorization. Can be called synchronously

Structs/ParseTextEntities.html.name: ParseTextEntities
Structs/ParseTextEntities.html.abstract: Parses Bold, Italic, Underline, Strikethrough, Code, Pre, PreCode, TextUrl and MentionName entities contained in the text. This is an offline method. Can be called before authorization. Can be called synchronously

Structs/GetFileMimeType.html.name: GetFileMimeType
Structs/GetFileMimeType.html.abstract: Returns the MIME type of a file, guessed by its extension. Returns an empty string on failure. This is an offline method. Can be called before authorization. Can be called synchronously

Structs/GetFileExtension.html.name: GetFileExtension
Structs/GetFileExtension.html.abstract: Returns the extension of a file, guessed by its MIME type. Returns an empty string on failure. This is an offline method. Can be called before authorization. Can be called synchronously

Structs/CleanFileName.html.name: CleanFileName
Structs/CleanFileName.html.abstract: Removes potentially dangerous characters from the name of a file. The encoding of the file name is supposed to be UTF-8. Returns an empty string on failure. This is an offline method. Can be called before authorization. Can be called synchronously

Structs/GetLanguagePackString.html.name: GetLanguagePackString
Structs/GetLanguagePackString.html.abstract: Returns a string stored in the local database from the specified localization target and language pack by its key. Returns a 404 error if the string is not found. This is an offline method. Can be called before authorization. Can be called synchronously

Structs/GetJsonValue.html.name: GetJsonValue
Structs/GetJsonValue.html.abstract: Converts a JSON-serialized string to corresponding JsonValue object. This is an offline method. Can be called before authorization. Can be called synchronously

Structs/GetJsonString.html.name: GetJsonString
Structs/GetJsonString.html.abstract: Converts a JsonValue object to corresponding JSON-serialized string. This is an offline method. Can be called before authorization. Can be called synchronously

Structs/SetPollAnswer.html.name: SetPollAnswer
Structs/SetPollAnswer.html.abstract: Changes the user answer to a poll. A poll in quiz mode can be answered only once

Structs/GetPollVoters.html.name: GetPollVoters
Structs/GetPollVoters.html.abstract: Returns users voted for the specified option in a non-anonymous polls. For the optimal performance the number of returned users is chosen by the library

Structs/StopPoll.html.name: StopPoll
Structs/StopPoll.html.abstract: Stops a poll. A poll in a message can be stopped when the message has can_be_edited flag set

Structs/GetLoginUrlInfo.html.name: GetLoginUrlInfo
Structs/GetLoginUrlInfo.html.abstract: Returns information about a button of type inlineKeyboardButtonTypeLoginUrl. The method needs to be called when the user presses the button

Structs/GetLoginUrl.html.name: GetLoginUrl
Structs/GetLoginUrl.html.abstract: Returns an HTTP URL which can be used to automatically authorize the user on a website after clicking an inline button of type inlineKeyboardButtonTypeLoginUrl. -Use the method getLoginUrlInfo to find whether a prior user confirmation is needed. If an error is returned, then the button must be handled as an ordinary URL button

Structs/GetInlineQueryResults.html.name: GetInlineQueryResults
Structs/GetInlineQueryResults.html.abstract: Sends an inline query to a bot and returns its results. Returns an error with code 502 if the bot fails to answer the query before the query timeout expires

Structs/AnswerInlineQuery.html.name: AnswerInlineQuery
Structs/AnswerInlineQuery.html.abstract: Sets the result of an inline query; for bots only

Structs/GetCallbackQueryAnswer.html.name: GetCallbackQueryAnswer
Structs/GetCallbackQueryAnswer.html.abstract: Sends a callback query to a bot and returns an answer. Returns an error with code 502 if the bot fails to answer the query before the query timeout expires

Structs/AnswerCallbackQuery.html.name: AnswerCallbackQuery
Structs/AnswerCallbackQuery.html.abstract: Sets the result of a callback query; for bots only

Structs/AnswerShippingQuery.html.name: AnswerShippingQuery
Structs/AnswerShippingQuery.html.abstract: Sets the result of a shipping query; for bots only

Structs/AnswerPreCheckoutQuery.html.name: AnswerPreCheckoutQuery
Structs/AnswerPreCheckoutQuery.html.abstract: Sets the result of a pre-checkout query; for bots only

Structs/SetGameScore.html.name: SetGameScore
Structs/SetGameScore.html.abstract: Updates the game score of the specified user in the game; for bots only

Structs/SetInlineGameScore.html.name: SetInlineGameScore
Structs/SetInlineGameScore.html.abstract: Updates the game score of the specified user in a game; for bots only

Structs/GetGameHighScores.html.name: GetGameHighScores
Structs/GetGameHighScores.html.abstract: Returns the high scores for a game and some part of the high score table in the range of the specified user; for bots only

Structs/GetInlineGameHighScores.html.name: GetInlineGameHighScores
Structs/GetInlineGameHighScores.html.abstract: Returns game high scores and some part of the high score table in the range of the specified user; for bots only

Structs/DeleteChatReplyMarkup.html.name: DeleteChatReplyMarkup
Structs/DeleteChatReplyMarkup.html.abstract: Deletes the default reply markup from a chat. Must be called after a one-time keyboard or a ForceReply reply markup has been used. UpdateChatReplyMarkup will be sent if the reply markup will be changed

Structs/SendChatAction.html.name: SendChatAction
Structs/SendChatAction.html.abstract: Sends a notification about user activity in a chat

Structs/OpenChat.html.name: OpenChat
Structs/OpenChat.html.abstract: Informs TDLib that the chat is opened by the user. Many useful activities depend on the chat being opened or closed (e.g., in supergroups and channels all updates are received only for opened chats)

Structs/CloseChat.html.name: CloseChat
Structs/CloseChat.html.abstract: Informs TDLib that the chat is closed by the user. Many useful activities depend on the chat being opened or closed

Structs/ViewMessages.html.name: ViewMessages
Structs/ViewMessages.html.abstract: Informs TDLib that messages are being viewed by the user. Many useful activities depend on whether the messages are currently being viewed or not (e.g., marking messages as read, incrementing a view counter, updating a view counter, removing deleted messages in supergroups and channels)

Structs/OpenMessageContent.html.name: OpenMessageContent
Structs/OpenMessageContent.html.abstract: Informs TDLib that the message content has been opened (e.g., the user has opened a photo, video, document, location or venue, or has listened to an audio file or voice note message). An updateMessageContentOpened update will be generated if something has changed

Structs/ReadAllChatMentions.html.name: ReadAllChatMentions
Structs/ReadAllChatMentions.html.abstract: Marks all mentions in a chat as read

Structs/CreatePrivateChat.html.name: CreatePrivateChat
Structs/CreatePrivateChat.html.abstract: Returns an existing chat corresponding to a given user

Structs/CreateBasicGroupChat.html.name: CreateBasicGroupChat
Structs/CreateBasicGroupChat.html.abstract: Returns an existing chat corresponding to a known basic group

Structs/CreateSupergroupChat.html.name: CreateSupergroupChat
Structs/CreateSupergroupChat.html.abstract: Returns an existing chat corresponding to a known supergroup or channel

Structs/CreateSecretChat.html.name: CreateSecretChat
Structs/CreateSecretChat.html.abstract: Returns an existing chat corresponding to a known secret chat

Structs/CreateNewBasicGroupChat.html.name: CreateNewBasicGroupChat
Structs/CreateNewBasicGroupChat.html.abstract: Creates a new basic group and sends a corresponding messageBasicGroupChatCreate. Returns the newly created chat

Structs/CreateNewSupergroupChat.html.name: CreateNewSupergroupChat
Structs/CreateNewSupergroupChat.html.abstract: Creates a new supergroup or channel and sends a corresponding messageSupergroupChatCreate. Returns the newly created chat

Structs/CreateNewSecretChat.html.name: CreateNewSecretChat
Structs/CreateNewSecretChat.html.abstract: Creates a new secret chat. Returns the newly created chat

Structs/UpgradeBasicGroupChatToSupergrou.name: UpgradeBasicGroupChatToSupergroupChat
Structs/UpgradeBasicGroupChatToSupergrou.abstract: Creates a new supergroup from an existing basic group and sends a corresponding messageChatUpgradeTo and messageChatUpgradeFrom; requires creator privileges. Deactivates the original basic group

Structs/SetChatChatList.html.name: SetChatChatList
Structs/SetChatChatList.html.abstract: Moves a chat to a different chat list. Current chat list of the chat must ne non-null

Structs/SetChatTitle.html.name: SetChatTitle
Structs/SetChatTitle.html.abstract: Changes the chat title. Supported only for basic groups, supergroups and channels. Requires can_change_info rights. The title will not be changed until the request to the server has been completed

Structs/SetChatPhoto.html.name: SetChatPhoto
Structs/SetChatPhoto.html.abstract: Changes the photo of a chat. Supported only for basic groups, supergroups and channels. Requires can_change_info rights. The photo will not be changed before request to the server has been completed

Structs/SetChatPermissions.html.name: SetChatPermissions
Structs/SetChatPermissions.html.abstract: Changes the chat members permissions. Supported only for basic groups and supergroups. Requires can_restrict_members administrator right

Structs/SetChatDraftMessage.html.name: SetChatDraftMessage
Structs/SetChatDraftMessage.html.abstract: Changes the draft message in a chat

Structs/SetChatNotificationSettings.html.name: SetChatNotificationSettings
Structs/SetChatNotificationSettings.html.abstract: Changes the notification settings of a chat. Notification settings of a chat with the current user (Saved Messages) can’t be changed

Structs/ToggleChatIsPinned.html.name: ToggleChatIsPinned
Structs/ToggleChatIsPinned.html.abstract: Changes the pinned state of a chat. You can pin up to GetOption(“pinned_chat_count_max”)/GetOption(“pinned_archived_chat_count_max”) non-secret chats and the same number of secret chats in the main/archive chat list

Structs/ToggleChatIsMarkedAsUnread.html.name: ToggleChatIsMarkedAsUnread
Structs/ToggleChatIsMarkedAsUnread.html.abstract: Changes the marked as unread state of a chat

Structs/ToggleChatDefaultDisableNotifica.name: ToggleChatDefaultDisableNotification
Structs/ToggleChatDefaultDisableNotifica.abstract: Changes the value of the default disable_notification parameter, used when a message is sent to a chat

Structs/SetChatClientData.html.name: SetChatClientData
Structs/SetChatClientData.html.abstract: Changes client data associated with a chat

Structs/SetChatDescription.html.name: SetChatDescription
Structs/SetChatDescription.html.abstract: Changes information about a chat. Available for basic groups, supergroups, and channels. Requires can_change_info rights

Structs/SetChatDiscussionGroup.html.name: SetChatDiscussionGroup
Structs/SetChatDiscussionGroup.html.abstract: Changes the discussion group of a channel chat; requires can_change_info rights in the channel if it is specified

Structs/SetChatLocation.html.name: SetChatLocation
Structs/SetChatLocation.html.abstract: Changes the location of a chat. Available only for some location-based supergroups, use supergroupFullInfo.can_set_location to check whether the method is allowed to use

Structs/SetChatSlowModeDelay.html.name: SetChatSlowModeDelay
Structs/SetChatSlowModeDelay.html.abstract: Changes the slow mode delay of a chat. Available only for supergroups; requires can_restrict_members rights

Structs/PinChatMessage.html.name: PinChatMessage
Structs/PinChatMessage.html.abstract: Pins a message in a chat; requires can_pin_messages rights

Structs/UnpinChatMessage.html.name: UnpinChatMessage
Structs/UnpinChatMessage.html.abstract: Removes the pinned message from a chat; requires can_pin_messages rights in the group or channel

Structs/JoinChat.html.name: JoinChat
Structs/JoinChat.html.abstract: Adds current user as a new member to a chat. Private and secret chats can’t be joined using this method

Structs/LeaveChat.html.name: LeaveChat
Structs/LeaveChat.html.abstract: Removes current user from chat members. Private and secret chats can’t be left using this method

Structs/AddChatMember.html.name: AddChatMember
Structs/AddChatMember.html.abstract: Adds a new member to a chat. Members can’t be added to private or secret chats. Members will not be added until the chat state has been synchronized with the server

Structs/AddChatMembers.html.name: AddChatMembers
Structs/AddChatMembers.html.abstract: Adds multiple new members to a chat. Currently this option is only available for supergroups and channels. This option can’t be used to join a chat. Members can’t be added to a channel if it has more than 200 members. Members will not be added until the chat state has been synchronized with the server

Structs/SetChatMemberStatus.html.name: SetChatMemberStatus
Structs/SetChatMemberStatus.html.abstract: Changes the status of a chat member, needs appropriate privileges. This function is currently not suitable for adding new members to the chat and transferring chat ownership; instead, use addChatMember or transferChatOwnership. The chat member status will not be changed until it has been synchronized with the server

Structs/CanTransferOwnership.html.name: CanTransferOwnership
Structs/CanTransferOwnership.html.abstract: Checks whether the current session can be used to transfer a chat ownership to another user

Structs/TransferChatOwnership.html.name: TransferChatOwnership
Structs/TransferChatOwnership.html.abstract: Changes the owner of a chat. The current user must be a current owner of the chat. Use the method canTransferOwnership to check whether the ownership can be transferred from the current session. Available only for supergroups and channel chats

Structs/GetChatMember.html.name: GetChatMember
Structs/GetChatMember.html.abstract: Returns information about a single member of a chat

Structs/SearchChatMembers.html.name: SearchChatMembers
Structs/SearchChatMembers.html.abstract: Searches for a specified query in the first name, last name and username of the members of a specified chat. Requires administrator rights in channels

Structs/GetChatAdministrators.html.name: GetChatAdministrators
Structs/GetChatAdministrators.html.abstract: Returns a list of administrators of the chat with their custom titles

Structs/GetChatNotificationSettingsExcep.name: GetChatNotificationSettingsExceptions
Structs/GetChatNotificationSettingsExcep.abstract: Returns list of chats with non-default notification settings

Structs/GetScopeNotificationSettings.htm.name: GetScopeNotificationSettings
Structs/GetScopeNotificationSettings.htm.abstract: Returns the notification settings for chats of a given type

Structs/SetScopeNotificationSettings.htm.name: SetScopeNotificationSettings
Structs/SetScopeNotificationSettings.htm.abstract: Changes notification settings for chats of a given type

Structs/ResetAllNotificationSettings.htm.name: ResetAllNotificationSettings
Structs/ResetAllNotificationSettings.htm.abstract: Resets all notification settings to their default values. By default, all chats are unmuted, the sound is set to “default” and message previews are shown

Structs/DownloadFile.html.name: DownloadFile
Structs/DownloadFile.html.abstract: Downloads a file from the cloud. Download progress and completion of the download will be notified through updateFile updates

Structs/GetFileDownloadedPrefixSize.html.name: GetFileDownloadedPrefixSize
Structs/GetFileDownloadedPrefixSize.html.abstract: Returns file downloaded prefix size from a given offset

Structs/CancelDownloadFile.html.name: CancelDownloadFile
Structs/CancelDownloadFile.html.abstract: Stops the downloading of a file. If a file has already been downloaded, does nothing

Structs/UploadFile.html.name: UploadFile
Structs/UploadFile.html.abstract: Asynchronously uploads a file to the cloud without sending it in a message. updateFile will be used to notify about upload progress and successful completion of the upload. The file will not have a persistent remote identifier until it will be sent in a message

Structs/CancelUploadFile.html.name: CancelUploadFile
Structs/CancelUploadFile.html.abstract: Stops the uploading of a file. Supported only for files uploaded by using uploadFile. For other files the behavior is undefined

Structs/WriteGeneratedFilePart.html.name: WriteGeneratedFilePart
Structs/WriteGeneratedFilePart.html.abstract: Writes a part of a generated file. This method is intended to be used only if the client has no direct access to TDLib’s file system, because it is usually slower than a direct write to the destination file

Structs/SetFileGenerationProgress.html.name: SetFileGenerationProgress
Structs/SetFileGenerationProgress.html.abstract: Informs TDLib on a file generation progress

Structs/ReadFilePart.html.name: ReadFilePart
Structs/ReadFilePart.html.abstract: Reads a part of a file from the TDLib file cache and returns read bytes. This method is intended to be used only if the client has no direct access to TDLib’s file system, because it is usually slower than a direct read from the file

Structs/DeleteFile.html.name: DeleteFile
Structs/DeleteFile.html.abstract: Deletes a file from the TDLib file cache

Structs/GenerateChatInviteLink.html.name: GenerateChatInviteLink
Structs/GenerateChatInviteLink.html.abstract: Generates a new invite link for a chat; the previously generated link is revoked. Available for basic groups, supergroups, and channels. Requires administrator privileges and can_invite_users right

Structs/CheckChatInviteLink.html.name: CheckChatInviteLink
Structs/CheckChatInviteLink.html.abstract: Checks the validity of an invite link for a chat and returns information about the corresponding chat

Structs/JoinChatByInviteLink.html.name: JoinChatByInviteLink
Structs/JoinChatByInviteLink.html.abstract: Uses an invite link to add the current user to the chat if possible. The new member will not be added until the chat state has been synchronized with the server

Structs/GetBlockedUsers.html.name: GetBlockedUsers
Structs/GetBlockedUsers.html.abstract: Returns users that were blocked by the current user

Structs/AddContact.html.name: AddContact
Structs/AddContact.html.abstract: Adds a user to the contact list or edits an existing contact by their user identifier

Structs/ImportContacts.html.name: ImportContacts
Structs/ImportContacts.html.abstract: Adds new contacts or edits existing contacts by their phone numbers; contacts’ user identifiers are ignored

Structs/SearchContacts.html.name: SearchContacts
Structs/SearchContacts.html.abstract: Searches for the specified query in the first names, last names and usernames of the known user contacts

Structs/GetImportedContactCount.html.name: GetImportedContactCount
Structs/GetImportedContactCount.html.abstract: Returns the total number of imported contacts

Structs/ChangeImportedContacts.html.name: ChangeImportedContacts
Structs/ChangeImportedContacts.html.abstract: Changes imported contacts using the list of current user contacts saved on the device. Imports newly added contacts and, if at least the file database is enabled, deletes recently deleted contacts. -Query result depends on the result of the previous query, so only one query is possible at the same time

Structs/ClearImportedContacts.html.name: ClearImportedContacts
Structs/ClearImportedContacts.html.abstract: Clears all imported contacts, contact list remains unchanged

Structs/SharePhoneNumber.html.name: SharePhoneNumber
Structs/SharePhoneNumber.html.abstract: Shares the phone number of the current user with a mutual contact. Supposed to be called when the user clicks on chatActionBarSharePhoneNumber

Structs/GetUserProfilePhotos.html.name: GetUserProfilePhotos
Structs/GetUserProfilePhotos.html.abstract: Returns the profile photos of a user. The result of this query may be outdated: some photos might have been deleted already

Structs/GetStickers.html.name: GetStickers
Structs/GetStickers.html.abstract: Returns stickers from the installed sticker sets that correspond to a given emoji. If the emoji is not empty, favorite and recently used stickers may also be returned

Structs/SearchStickers.html.name: SearchStickers
Structs/SearchStickers.html.abstract: Searches for stickers from public sticker sets that correspond to a given emoji

Structs/GetInstalledStickerSets.html.name: GetInstalledStickerSets
Structs/GetInstalledStickerSets.html.abstract: Returns a list of installed sticker sets

Structs/GetArchivedStickerSets.html.name: GetArchivedStickerSets
Structs/GetArchivedStickerSets.html.abstract: Returns a list of archived sticker sets

Structs/GetTrendingStickerSets.html.name: GetTrendingStickerSets
Structs/GetTrendingStickerSets.html.abstract: Returns a list of trending sticker sets

Structs/GetAttachedStickerSets.html.name: GetAttachedStickerSets
Structs/GetAttachedStickerSets.html.abstract: Returns a list of sticker sets attached to a file. Currently only photos and videos can have attached sticker sets

Structs/GetStickerSet.html.name: GetStickerSet
Structs/GetStickerSet.html.abstract: Returns information about a sticker set by its identifier

Structs/SearchStickerSet.html.name: SearchStickerSet
Structs/SearchStickerSet.html.abstract: Searches for a sticker set by its name

Structs/SearchInstalledStickerSets.html.name: SearchInstalledStickerSets
Structs/SearchInstalledStickerSets.html.abstract: Searches for installed sticker sets by looking for specified query in their title and name

Structs/SearchStickerSets.html.name: SearchStickerSets
Structs/SearchStickerSets.html.abstract: Searches for ordinary sticker sets by looking for specified query in their title and name. Excludes installed sticker sets from the results

Structs/ViewTrendingStickerSets.html.name: ViewTrendingStickerSets
Structs/ViewTrendingStickerSets.html.abstract: Informs the server that some trending sticker sets have been viewed by the user

Structs/ReorderInstalledStickerSets.html.name: ReorderInstalledStickerSets
Structs/ReorderInstalledStickerSets.html.abstract: Changes the order of installed sticker sets

Structs/GetRecentStickers.html.name: GetRecentStickers
Structs/GetRecentStickers.html.abstract: Returns a list of recently used stickers

Structs/AddRecentSticker.html.name: AddRecentSticker
Structs/AddRecentSticker.html.abstract: Manually adds a new sticker to the list of recently used stickers. The new sticker is added to the top of the list. If the sticker was already in the list, it is removed from the list first. Only stickers belonging to a sticker set can be added to this list

Structs/RemoveRecentSticker.html.name: RemoveRecentSticker
Structs/RemoveRecentSticker.html.abstract: Removes a sticker from the list of recently used stickers

Structs/ClearRecentStickers.html.name: ClearRecentStickers
Structs/ClearRecentStickers.html.abstract: Clears the list of recently used stickers

Structs/AddFavoriteSticker.html.name: AddFavoriteSticker
Structs/AddFavoriteSticker.html.abstract: Adds a new sticker to the list of favorite stickers. The new sticker is added to the top of the list. If the sticker was already in the list, it is removed from the list first. Only stickers belonging to a sticker set can be added to this list

Structs/RemoveFavoriteSticker.html.name: RemoveFavoriteSticker
Structs/RemoveFavoriteSticker.html.abstract: Removes a sticker from the list of favorite stickers

Structs/GetStickerEmojis.html.name: GetStickerEmojis
Structs/GetStickerEmojis.html.abstract: Returns emoji corresponding to a sticker. The list is only for informational purposes, because a sticker is always sent with a fixed emoji from the corresponding Sticker object

Structs/SearchEmojis.html.name: SearchEmojis
Structs/SearchEmojis.html.abstract: Searches for emojis by keywords. Supported only if the file database is enabled

Structs/GetEmojiSuggestionsUrl.html.name: GetEmojiSuggestionsUrl
Structs/GetEmojiSuggestionsUrl.html.abstract: Returns an HTTP URL which can be used to automatically log in to the translation platform and suggest new emoji replacements. The URL will be valid for 30 seconds after generation

Structs/AddSavedAnimation.html.name: AddSavedAnimation
Structs/AddSavedAnimation.html.abstract: Manually adds a new animation to the list of saved animations. The new animation is added to the beginning of the list. If the animation was already in the list, it is removed first. Only non-secret video animations with MIME type “video/mp4” can be added to the list

Structs/RemoveSavedAnimation.html.name: RemoveSavedAnimation
Structs/RemoveSavedAnimation.html.abstract: Removes an animation from the list of saved animations

Structs/GetRecentInlineBots.html.name: GetRecentInlineBots
Structs/GetRecentInlineBots.html.abstract: Returns up to 20 recently used inline bots in the order of their last usage

Structs/SearchHashtags.html.name: SearchHashtags
Structs/SearchHashtags.html.abstract: Searches for recently used hashtags by their prefix

Structs/RemoveRecentHashtag.html.name: RemoveRecentHashtag
Structs/RemoveRecentHashtag.html.abstract: Removes a hashtag from the list of recently used hashtags

Structs/GetWebPagePreview.html.name: GetWebPagePreview
Structs/GetWebPagePreview.html.abstract: Returns a web page preview by the text of the message. Do not call this function too often. Returns a 404 error if the web page has no preview

Structs/GetWebPageInstantView.html.name: GetWebPageInstantView
Structs/GetWebPageInstantView.html.abstract: Returns an instant view version of a web page if available. Returns a 404 error if the web page has no instant view page

Structs/SetProfilePhoto.html.name: SetProfilePhoto
Structs/SetProfilePhoto.html.abstract: Uploads a new profile photo for the current user. If something changes, updateUser will be sent

Structs/DeleteProfilePhoto.html.name: DeleteProfilePhoto
Structs/DeleteProfilePhoto.html.abstract: Deletes a profile photo. If something changes, updateUser will be sent

Structs/SetName.html.name: SetName
Structs/SetName.html.abstract: Changes the first and last name of the current user. If something changes, updateUser will be sent

Structs/SetBio.html.name: SetBio
Structs/SetBio.html.abstract: Changes the bio of the current user

Structs/SetUsername.html.name: SetUsername
Structs/SetUsername.html.abstract: Changes the username of the current user. If something changes, updateUser will be sent

Structs/ChangePhoneNumber.html.name: ChangePhoneNumber
Structs/ChangePhoneNumber.html.abstract: Changes the phone number of the user and sends an authentication code to the user’s new phone number. On success, returns information about the sent code

Structs/ResendChangePhoneNumberCode.html.name: ResendChangePhoneNumberCode
Structs/ResendChangePhoneNumberCode.html.abstract: Re-sends the authentication code sent to confirm a new phone number for the user. Works only if the previously received authenticationCodeInfo next_code_type was not null

Structs/CheckChangePhoneNumberCode.html.name: CheckChangePhoneNumberCode
Structs/CheckChangePhoneNumberCode.html.abstract: Checks the authentication code sent to confirm a new phone number of the user

Structs/GetActiveSessions.html.name: GetActiveSessions
Structs/GetActiveSessions.html.abstract: Returns all active sessions of the current user

Structs/TerminateSession.html.name: TerminateSession
Structs/TerminateSession.html.abstract: Terminates a session of the current user

Structs/TerminateAllOtherSessions.html.name: TerminateAllOtherSessions
Structs/TerminateAllOtherSessions.html.abstract: Terminates all other sessions of the current user

Structs/GetConnectedWebsites.html.name: GetConnectedWebsites
Structs/GetConnectedWebsites.html.abstract: Returns all website where the current user used Telegram to log in

Structs/DisconnectWebsite.html.name: DisconnectWebsite
Structs/DisconnectWebsite.html.abstract: Disconnects website from the current user’s Telegram account

Structs/DisconnectAllWebsites.html.name: DisconnectAllWebsites
Structs/DisconnectAllWebsites.html.abstract: Disconnects all websites from the current user’s Telegram account

Structs/SetSupergroupUsername.html.name: SetSupergroupUsername
Structs/SetSupergroupUsername.html.abstract: Changes the username of a supergroup or channel, requires owner privileges in the supergroup or channel

Structs/SetSupergroupStickerSet.html.name: SetSupergroupStickerSet
Structs/SetSupergroupStickerSet.html.abstract: Changes the sticker set of a supergroup; requires can_change_info rights

Structs/ToggleSupergroupSignMessages.htm.name: ToggleSupergroupSignMessages
Structs/ToggleSupergroupSignMessages.htm.abstract: Toggles sender signatures messages sent in a channel; requires can_change_info rights

Structs/ToggleSupergroupIsAllHistoryAvai.name: ToggleSupergroupIsAllHistoryAvailable
Structs/ToggleSupergroupIsAllHistoryAvai.abstract: Toggles whether the message history of a supergroup is available to new members; requires can_change_info rights

Structs/ReportSupergroupSpam.html.name: ReportSupergroupSpam
Structs/ReportSupergroupSpam.html.abstract: Reports some messages from a user in a supergroup as spam; requires administrator rights in the supergroup

Structs/GetSupergroupMembers.html.name: GetSupergroupMembers
Structs/GetSupergroupMembers.html.abstract: Returns information about members or banned users in a supergroup or channel. Can be used only if SupergroupFullInfo.can_get_members == true; additionally, administrator privileges may be required for some filters

Structs/DeleteSupergroup.html.name: DeleteSupergroup
Structs/DeleteSupergroup.html.abstract: Deletes a supergroup or channel along with all messages in the corresponding chat. This will release the supergroup or channel username and remove all members; requires owner privileges in the supergroup or channel. Chats with more than 1000 members can’t be deleted using this method

Structs/CloseSecretChat.html.name: CloseSecretChat
Structs/CloseSecretChat.html.abstract: Closes a secret chat, effectively transferring its state to secretChatStateClosed

Structs/GetChatEventLog.html.name: GetChatEventLog
Structs/GetChatEventLog.html.abstract: Returns a list of service actions taken by chat members and administrators in the last 48 hours. Available only for supergroups and channels. Requires administrator rights. Returns results in reverse chronological order (i. e., in order of decreasing event_id)

Structs/GetPaymentForm.html.name: GetPaymentForm
Structs/GetPaymentForm.html.abstract: Returns an invoice payment form. This method should be called when the user presses inlineKeyboardButtonBuy

Structs/ValidateOrderInfo.html.name: ValidateOrderInfo
Structs/ValidateOrderInfo.html.abstract: Validates the order information provided by a user and returns the available shipping options for a flexible invoice

Structs/SendPaymentForm.html.name: SendPaymentForm
Structs/SendPaymentForm.html.abstract: Sends a filled-out payment form to the bot for final verification

Structs/DeleteSavedCredentials.html.name: DeleteSavedCredentials
Structs/DeleteSavedCredentials.html.abstract: Deletes saved credentials for all payment provider bots

Structs/GetSupportUser.html.name: GetSupportUser
Structs/GetSupportUser.html.abstract: Returns a user that can be contacted to get support

Structs/GetBackgroundUrl.html.name: GetBackgroundUrl
Structs/GetBackgroundUrl.html.abstract: Constructs a persistent HTTP URL for a background

Structs/SearchBackground.html.name: SearchBackground
Structs/SearchBackground.html.abstract: Searches for a background by its name

Structs/SetBackground.html.name: SetBackground
Structs/SetBackground.html.abstract: Changes the background selected by the user; adds background to the list of installed backgrounds

Structs/RemoveBackground.html.name: RemoveBackground
Structs/RemoveBackground.html.abstract: Removes background from the list of installed backgrounds

Structs/ResetBackgrounds.html.name: ResetBackgrounds
Structs/ResetBackgrounds.html.abstract: Resets list of installed backgrounds to its default value

Structs/GetLocalizationTargetInfo.html.name: GetLocalizationTargetInfo
Structs/GetLocalizationTargetInfo.html.abstract: Returns information about the current localization target. This is an offline request if only_local is true. Can be called before authorization

Structs/GetLanguagePackInfo.html.name: GetLanguagePackInfo
Structs/GetLanguagePackInfo.html.abstract: Returns information about a language pack. Returned language pack identifier may be different from a provided one. Can be called before authorization

Structs/GetLanguagePackStrings.html.name: GetLanguagePackStrings
Structs/GetLanguagePackStrings.html.abstract: Returns strings from a language pack in the current localization target by their keys. Can be called before authorization

Structs/SynchronizeLanguagePack.html.name: SynchronizeLanguagePack
Structs/SynchronizeLanguagePack.html.abstract: Fetches the latest versions of all strings from a language pack in the current localization target from the server. This method doesn’t need to be called explicitly for the current used/base language packs. Can be called before authorization

Structs/AddCustomServerLanguagePack.html.name: AddCustomServerLanguagePack
Structs/AddCustomServerLanguagePack.html.abstract: Adds a custom server language pack to the list of installed language packs in current localization target. Can be called before authorization

Structs/SetCustomLanguagePack.html.name: SetCustomLanguagePack
Structs/SetCustomLanguagePack.html.abstract: Adds or changes a custom local language pack to the current localization target

Structs/EditCustomLanguagePackInfo.html.name: EditCustomLanguagePackInfo
Structs/EditCustomLanguagePackInfo.html.abstract: Edits information about a custom local language pack in the current localization target. Can be called before authorization

Structs/SetCustomLanguagePackString.html.name: SetCustomLanguagePackString
Structs/SetCustomLanguagePackString.html.abstract: Adds, edits or deletes a string in a custom local language pack. Can be called before authorization

Structs/DeleteLanguagePack.html.name: DeleteLanguagePack
Structs/DeleteLanguagePack.html.abstract: Deletes all information about a language pack in the current localization target. The language pack which is currently in use (including base language pack) or is being synchronized can’t be deleted. Can be called before authorization

Structs/RegisterDevice.html.name: RegisterDevice
Structs/RegisterDevice.html.abstract: Registers the currently used device for receiving push notifications. Returns a globally unique identifier of the push notification subscription

Structs/ProcessPushNotification.html.name: ProcessPushNotification
Structs/ProcessPushNotification.html.abstract: Handles a push notification. Returns error with code 406 if the push notification is not supported and connection to the server is required to fetch new data. Can be called before authorization

Structs/GetPushReceiverId.html.name: GetPushReceiverId
Structs/GetPushReceiverId.html.abstract: Returns a globally unique push notification subscription identifier for identification of an account, which has received a push notification. This is an offline method. Can be called before authorization. Can be called synchronously

Structs/GetRecentlyVisitedTMeUrls.html.name: GetRecentlyVisitedTMeUrls
Structs/GetRecentlyVisitedTMeUrls.html.abstract: Returns t.me URLs recently visited by a newly registered user

Structs/GetOption.html.name: GetOption
Structs/GetOption.html.abstract: Returns the value of an option by its name. (Check the list of available options on https://core.telegram.org/tdlib/options.) Can be called before authorization

Structs/SetOption.html.name: SetOption
Structs/SetOption.html.abstract: Sets the value of an option. (Check the list of available options on https://core.telegram.org/tdlib/options.) Only writable options can be set. Can be called before authorization

Structs/SetAccountTtl.html.name: SetAccountTtl
Structs/SetAccountTtl.html.abstract: Changes the period of inactivity after which the account of the current user will automatically be deleted

Structs/GetAccountTtl.html.name: GetAccountTtl
Structs/GetAccountTtl.html.abstract: Returns the period of inactivity after which the account of the current user will automatically be deleted

Structs/DeleteAccount.html.name: DeleteAccount
Structs/DeleteAccount.html.abstract: Deletes the account of the current user, deleting all information associated with the user from the server. The phone number of the account can be used to create a new account. Can be called before authorization when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitPassword

Structs/RemoveChatActionBar.html.name: RemoveChatActionBar
Structs/RemoveChatActionBar.html.abstract: Removes a chat action bar without any other action

Structs/ReportChat.html.name: ReportChat
Structs/ReportChat.html.abstract: Reports a chat to the Telegram moderators. Supported only for supergroups, channels, or private chats with bots, since other chats can’t be checked by moderators, or when the report is done from the chat action bar

Structs/GetChatStatisticsUrl.html.name: GetChatStatisticsUrl
Structs/GetChatStatisticsUrl.html.abstract: Returns an HTTP URL with the chat statistics. Currently this method can be used only for channels. Can be used only if SupergroupFullInfo.can_view_statistics == true

Structs/GetStorageStatistics.html.name: GetStorageStatistics
Structs/GetStorageStatistics.html.abstract: Returns storage usage statistics. Can be called before authorization

Structs/GetStorageStatisticsFast.html.name: GetStorageStatisticsFast
Structs/GetStorageStatisticsFast.html.abstract: Quickly returns approximate storage usage statistics. Can be called before authorization

Structs/OptimizeStorage.html.name: OptimizeStorage
Structs/OptimizeStorage.html.abstract: Optimizes storage usage, i.e. deletes some files and returns new storage usage statistics. Secret thumbnails can’t be deleted

Structs/SetNetworkType.html.name: SetNetworkType
Structs/SetNetworkType.html.abstract: Sets the current network type. Can be called before authorization. Calling this method forces all network connections to reopen, mitigating the delay in switching between different networks, so it should be called whenever the network is changed, even if the network type remains the same. -Network type is used to check whether the library can use the network at all and also for collecting detailed network data usage statistics

Structs/GetNetworkStatistics.html.name: GetNetworkStatistics
Structs/GetNetworkStatistics.html.abstract: Returns network data usage statistics. Can be called before authorization

Structs/AddNetworkStatistics.html.name: AddNetworkStatistics
Structs/AddNetworkStatistics.html.abstract: Adds the specified data to data usage statistics. Can be called before authorization

Structs/ResetNetworkStatistics.html.name: ResetNetworkStatistics
Structs/ResetNetworkStatistics.html.abstract: Resets all network data usage statistics to zero. Can be called before authorization

Structs/GetAutoDownloadSettingsPresets.h.name: GetAutoDownloadSettingsPresets
Structs/GetAutoDownloadSettingsPresets.h.abstract: Returns auto-download settings presets for the currently logged in user

Structs/GetPassportElement.html.name: GetPassportElement
Structs/GetPassportElement.html.abstract: Returns one of the available Telegram Passport elements

Structs/SetPassportElement.html.name: SetPassportElement
Structs/SetPassportElement.html.abstract: Adds an element to the user’s Telegram Passport. May return an error with a message “PHONE_VERIFICATION_NEEDED” or “EMAIL_VERIFICATION_NEEDED” if the chosen phone number or the chosen email address must be verified first

Structs/SetPassportElementErrors.html.name: SetPassportElementErrors
Structs/SetPassportElementErrors.html.abstract: Informs the user that some of the elements in their Telegram Passport contain errors; for bots only. The user will not be able to resend the elements, until the errors are fixed

Structs/GetPreferredCountryLanguage.html.name: GetPreferredCountryLanguage
Structs/GetPreferredCountryLanguage.html.abstract: Returns an IETF language tag of the language preferred in the country, which should be used to fill native fields in Telegram Passport personal details. Returns a 404 error if unknown

Structs/SendPhoneNumberVerificationCode..name: SendPhoneNumberVerificationCode
Structs/SendPhoneNumberVerificationCode..abstract: Sends a code to verify a phone number to be added to a user’s Telegram Passport

Structs/ResendPhoneNumberVerificationCod.name: ResendPhoneNumberVerificationCode
Structs/ResendPhoneNumberVerificationCod.abstract: Re-sends the code to verify a phone number to be added to a user’s Telegram Passport

Structs/CheckPhoneNumberVerificationCode.name: CheckPhoneNumberVerificationCode
Structs/CheckPhoneNumberVerificationCode.abstract: Checks the phone number verification code for Telegram Passport

Structs/SendEmailAddressVerificationCode.name: SendEmailAddressVerificationCode
Structs/SendEmailAddressVerificationCode.abstract: Sends a code to verify an email address to be added to a user’s Telegram Passport

Structs/ResendEmailAddressVerificationCo.name: ResendEmailAddressVerificationCode
Structs/ResendEmailAddressVerificationCo.abstract: Re-sends the code to verify an email address to be added to a user’s Telegram Passport

Structs/CheckEmailAddressVerificationCod.name: CheckEmailAddressVerificationCode
Structs/CheckEmailAddressVerificationCod.abstract: Checks the email address verification code for Telegram Passport

Structs/GetPassportAuthorizationForm.htm.name: GetPassportAuthorizationForm
Structs/GetPassportAuthorizationForm.htm.abstract: Returns a Telegram Passport authorization form for sharing data with a service

Structs/GetPassportAuthorizationFormAvai.name: GetPassportAuthorizationFormAvailableElements
Structs/GetPassportAuthorizationFormAvai.abstract: Returns already available Telegram Passport elements suitable for completing a Telegram Passport authorization form. Result can be received only once for each authorization form

Structs/SendPassportAuthorizationForm.ht.name: SendPassportAuthorizationForm
Structs/SendPassportAuthorizationForm.ht.abstract: Sends a Telegram Passport authorization form, effectively sharing data with the service. This method must be called after getPassportAuthorizationFormAvailableElements if some previously available elements need to be used

Structs/SendPhoneNumberConfirmationCode..name: SendPhoneNumberConfirmationCode
Structs/SendPhoneNumberConfirmationCode..abstract: Sends phone number confirmation code. Should be called when user presses “https://t.me/confirmphone?phone=*******&hash=**********” or “tg://confirmphone?phone=****&hash=*******” link

Structs/SetBotUpdatesStatus.html.name: SetBotUpdatesStatus
Structs/SetBotUpdatesStatus.html.abstract: Informs the server about the number of pending bot updates if they haven’t been processed for a long time; for bots only

Structs/UploadStickerFile.html.name: UploadStickerFile
Structs/UploadStickerFile.html.abstract: Uploads a PNG image with a sticker; for bots only; returns the uploaded file

Structs/CreateNewStickerSet.html.name: CreateNewStickerSet
Structs/CreateNewStickerSet.html.abstract: Creates a new sticker set; for bots only. Returns the newly created sticker set

Structs/AddStickerToSet.html.name: AddStickerToSet
Structs/AddStickerToSet.html.abstract: Adds a new sticker to a set; for bots only. Returns the sticker set

Structs/SetStickerPositionInSet.html.name: SetStickerPositionInSet
Structs/SetStickerPositionInSet.html.abstract: Changes the position of a sticker in the set to which it belongs; for bots only. The sticker set must have been created by the bot

Structs/RemoveStickerFromSet.html.name: RemoveStickerFromSet
Structs/RemoveStickerFromSet.html.abstract: Removes a sticker from the set to which it belongs; for bots only. The sticker set must have been created by the bot

Structs/GetMapThumbnailFile.html.name: GetMapThumbnailFile
Structs/GetMapThumbnailFile.html.abstract: Returns information about a file with a map thumbnail in PNG format. Only map thumbnail files with size less than 1MB can be downloaded

Structs/SendCustomRequest.html.name: SendCustomRequest
Structs/SendCustomRequest.html.abstract: Sends a custom request; for bots only

Structs/AnswerCustomQuery.html.name: AnswerCustomQuery
Structs/AnswerCustomQuery.html.abstract: Answers a custom query; for bots only

Structs/SetAlarm.html.name: SetAlarm
Structs/SetAlarm.html.abstract: Succeeds after a specified amount of time has passed. Can be called before authorization. Can be called before initialization

Structs/GetCountryCode.html.name: GetCountryCode
Structs/GetCountryCode.html.abstract: Uses current user IP to found their country. Returns two-letter ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code. Can be called before authorization

Structs/GetInviteText.html.name: GetInviteText
Structs/GetInviteText.html.abstract: Returns the default text for invitation messages to be used as a placeholder when the current user invites friends to Telegram

Structs/GetDeepLinkInfo.html.name: GetDeepLinkInfo
Structs/GetDeepLinkInfo.html.abstract: Returns information about a tg:// deep link. Use “tg://need_update_for_some_feature” or “tg:some_unsupported_feature” for testing. Returns a 404 error for unknown links. Can be called before authorization

Structs/GetApplicationConfig.html.name: GetApplicationConfig
Structs/GetApplicationConfig.html.abstract: Returns application config, provided by the server. Can be called before authorization

Structs/SaveApplicationLogEvent.html.name: SaveApplicationLogEvent
Structs/SaveApplicationLogEvent.html.abstract: Saves application log event on the server. Can be called before authorization

Structs/AddProxy.html.name: AddProxy
Structs/AddProxy.html.abstract: Adds a proxy server for network requests. Can be called before authorization

Structs/EditProxy.html.name: EditProxy
Structs/EditProxy.html.abstract: Edits an existing proxy server for network requests. Can be called before authorization

Structs/EnableProxy.html.name: EnableProxy
Structs/EnableProxy.html.abstract: Enables a proxy. Only one proxy can be enabled at a time. Can be called before authorization

Structs/DisableProxy.html.name: DisableProxy
Structs/DisableProxy.html.abstract: Disables the currently enabled proxy. Can be called before authorization

Structs/RemoveProxy.html.name: RemoveProxy
Structs/RemoveProxy.html.abstract: Removes a proxy server. Can be called before authorization

Structs/GetProxies.html.name: GetProxies
Structs/GetProxies.html.abstract: Returns list of proxies that are currently set up. Can be called before authorization

Structs/GetProxyLink.html.name: GetProxyLink
Structs/GetProxyLink.html.abstract: Returns an HTTPS link, which can be used to add a proxy. Available only for SOCKS5 and MTProto proxies. Can be called before authorization

Structs/PingProxy.html.name: PingProxy
Structs/PingProxy.html.abstract: Computes time needed to receive a response from a Telegram server through a proxy. Can be called before authorization

Structs/SetLogStream.html.name: SetLogStream
Structs/SetLogStream.html.abstract: Sets new log stream for internal logging of TDLib. This is an offline method. Can be called before authorization. Can be called synchronously

Structs/GetLogStream.html.name: GetLogStream
Structs/GetLogStream.html.abstract: Returns information about currently used log stream for internal logging of TDLib. This is an offline method. Can be called before authorization. Can be called synchronously

Structs/SetLogVerbosityLevel.html.name: SetLogVerbosityLevel
Structs/SetLogVerbosityLevel.html.abstract: Sets the verbosity level of the internal logging of TDLib. This is an offline method. Can be called before authorization. Can be called synchronously

Structs/GetLogVerbosityLevel.html.name: GetLogVerbosityLevel
Structs/GetLogVerbosityLevel.html.abstract: Returns current verbosity level of the internal logging of TDLib. This is an offline method. Can be called before authorization. Can be called synchronously

Structs/GetLogTags.html.name: GetLogTags
Structs/GetLogTags.html.abstract: Returns list of available TDLib internal log tags, for example, [“actor”, “binlog”, “connections”, “notifications”, “proxy”]. This is an offline method. Can be called before authorization. Can be called synchronously

Structs/SetLogTagVerbosityLevel.html.name: SetLogTagVerbosityLevel
Structs/SetLogTagVerbosityLevel.html.abstract: Sets the verbosity level for a specified TDLib internal log tag. This is an offline method. Can be called before authorization. Can be called synchronously

Structs/GetLogTagVerbosityLevel.html.name: GetLogTagVerbosityLevel
Structs/GetLogTagVerbosityLevel.html.abstract: Returns current verbosity level for a specified TDLib internal log tag. This is an offline method. Can be called before authorization. Can be called synchronously

Structs/AddLogMessage.html.name: AddLogMessage
Structs/AddLogMessage.html.abstract: Adds a message to TDLib internal log. This is an offline method. Can be called before authorization. Can be called synchronously

Structs/TestCallEmpty.html.name: TestCallEmpty
Structs/TestCallEmpty.html.abstract: Does nothing; for testing only. This is an offline method. Can be called before authorization

Structs/TestCallString.html.name: TestCallString
Structs/TestCallString.html.abstract: Returns the received string; for testing only. This is an offline method. Can be called before authorization

Structs/TestCallBytes.html.name: TestCallBytes
Structs/TestCallBytes.html.abstract: Returns the received bytes; for testing only. This is an offline method. Can be called before authorization

Structs/TestCallVectorInt.html.name: TestCallVectorInt
Structs/TestCallVectorInt.html.abstract: Returns the received vector of numbers; for testing only. This is an offline method. Can be called before authorization

Structs/TestCallVectorIntObject.html.name: TestCallVectorIntObject
Structs/TestCallVectorIntObject.html.abstract: Returns the received vector of objects containing a number; for testing only. This is an offline method. Can be called before authorization

Structs/TestCallVectorString.html.name: TestCallVectorString
Structs/TestCallVectorString.html.abstract: Returns the received vector of strings; for testing only. This is an offline method. Can be called before authorization

Structs/TestCallVectorStringObject.html.name: TestCallVectorStringObject
Structs/TestCallVectorStringObject.html.abstract: Returns the received vector of objects containing a string; for testing only. This is an offline method. Can be called before authorization

Structs/TestSquareInt.html.name: TestSquareInt
Structs/TestSquareInt.html.abstract: Returns the squared received number; for testing only. This is an offline method. Can be called before authorization

Structs/TestNetwork.html.name: TestNetwork
Structs/TestNetwork.html.abstract: Sends a simple network request to the Telegram servers; for testing only. Can be called before authorization

Structs/TestProxy.html.name: TestProxy
Structs/TestProxy.html.abstract: Sends a simple network request to the Telegram servers via proxy; for testing only. Can be called before authorization

Structs/TestGetDifference.html.name: TestGetDifference
Structs/TestGetDifference.html.abstract: Forces an updates.getDifference call to the Telegram servers; for testing only

Structs/TestUseUpdate.html.name: TestUseUpdate
Structs/TestUseUpdate.html.abstract: Does nothing and ensures that the Update object is used; for testing only. This is an offline method. Can be called before authorization

Structs/TestReturnError.html.name: TestReturnError
Structs/TestReturnError.html.abstract: Returns the specified error and ensures that the Error object is used; for testing only. This is an offline method. Can be called before authorization. Can be called synchronously

Enums/LogStream.html#/s:5TDLib9LogStream.name: default
Enums/LogStream.html#/s:5TDLib9LogStream.abstract: The log is written to stderr or an OS specific log

Enums/LogStream.html#/s:5TDLib9LogStream.name: file(path:maxFileSize:)
Enums/LogStream.html#/s:5TDLib9LogStream.abstract: The log is written to a file

Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO10new.name: newMessage(message:)
Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO10new.abstract: A new message was received; can also be an outgoing message

Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO23mes.name: messageSendAcknowledged(chatId:messageId:)
Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO23mes.abstract: A request to send a message has reached the Telegram server. This doesn’t mean that the message will be sent successfully or even that the send message request will be processed. This update will be sent only if the option “use_quick_ack” is set to true. This update may be sent multiple times for the same message

Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO17mes.name: messageSendFailed(message:oldMessageId:errorCode:errorMessage:)
Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO17mes.abstract: A message failed to send. Be aware that some messages being sent can be irrecoverably deleted, in which case updateDeleteMessages will be received instead of this update

Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO13mes.name: messageEdited(chatId:messageId:editDate:replyMarkup:)
Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO13mes.abstract: A message was edited. Changes in the message content will come in a separate updateMessageContent

Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO12mes.name: messageViews(chatId:messageId:views:)
Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO12mes.abstract: The view count of the message has changed

Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO20mes.name: messageContentOpened(chatId:messageId:)
Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO20mes.abstract: The message content was opened. Updates voice note messages to “listened”, video note messages to “viewed” and starts the TTL timer for self-destructing messages

Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO18mes.name: messageMentionRead(chatId:messageId:unreadMentionCount:)
Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO18mes.abstract: A message with an unread mention was read

Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO25mes.name: messageLiveLocationViewed(chatId:messageId:)
Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO25mes.abstract: A message with a live location was viewed. When the update is received, the client is supposed to update the live location

Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO7newC.name: newChat(chat:)
Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO7newC.abstract: A new chat has been loaded/created. This update is guaranteed to come before the chat identifier is returned to the client. The chat field changes will be reported through separate updates

Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO12cha.name: chatChatList(chatId:chatList:)
Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO12cha.abstract: The list to which the chat belongs was changed. This update is guaranteed to be sent only when chat.order == 0 and the current or the new chat list is null

Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO9chat.name: chatTitle(chatId:title:)
Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO9chat.abstract: The title of a chat was changed

Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO15cha.name: chatLastMessage(chatId:lastMessage:order:)
Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO15cha.abstract: The last message of a chat was changed. If last_message is null, then the last message in the chat became unknown. Some new unknown messages might be added to the chat in this case

Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO9chat.name: chatOrder(chatId:order:)
Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO9chat.abstract: The order of the chat in the chat list has changed. Instead of this update updateChatLastMessage, updateChatIsPinned, updateChatDraftMessage, or updateChatIsSponsored might be sent

Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO20cha.name: chatIsMarkedAsUnread(chatId:isMarkedAsUnread:)
Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO20cha.abstract: A chat was marked as unread or was read

Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO30cha.name: chatDefaultDisableNotification(chatId:defaultDisableNotification:)
Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO30cha.abstract: The value of the default disable_notification parameter, used when a message is sent to the chat, was changed

Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO13cha.name: chatReadInbox(chatId:lastReadInboxMessageId:unreadCount:)
Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO13cha.abstract: Incoming messages were read or number of unread messages has been changed

Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO24cha.name: chatNotificationSettings(chatId:notificationSettings:)
Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO24cha.abstract: Notification settings for a chat were changed

Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO25sco.name: scopeNotificationSettings(scope:notificationSettings:)
Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO25sco.abstract: Notification settings for some type of chats were updated

Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO15cha.name: chatReplyMarkup(chatId:replyMarkupMessageId:)
Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO15cha.abstract: The default chat reply markup was changed. Can occur because new messages with reply markup were received or because an old reply markup was hidden by the user

Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO16cha.name: chatDraftMessage(chatId:draftMessage:order:)
Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO16cha.abstract: A chat draft has changed. Be aware that the update may come in the currently opened chat but with old content of the draft. If the user has changed the content of the draft, this update shouldn’t be applied

Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO21cha.name: chatOnlineMemberCount(chatId:onlineMemberCount:)
Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO21cha.abstract: The number of online group members has changed. This update with non-zero count is sent only for currently opened chats. There is no guarantee that it will be sent just after the count has changed

Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO17not.name: notificationGroup(notificationGroupId:type:chatId:notificationSettingsChatId:isSilent:totalCount:addedNotifications:removedNotificationIds:)
Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO17not.abstract: A list of active notifications in a notification group has changed

Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO19act.name: activeNotifications(groups:)
Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO19act.abstract: Contains active notifications that was shown on previous application launches. This update is sent only if the message database is used. In that case it comes once before any updateNotification and updateNotificationGroup update

Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO24hav.name: havePendingNotifications(haveDelayedNotifications:haveUnreceivedNotifications:)
Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO24hav.abstract: Describes whether there are some pending notification updates. Can be used to prevent application from killing, while there are some pending notifications

Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO14use.name: userChatAction(chatId:userId:action:)
Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO14use.abstract: User activity in the chat has changed

Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO4user.name: user(user:)
Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO4user.abstract: Some data of a user has changed. This update is guaranteed to come before the user identifier is returned to the client

Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO10bas.name: basicGroup(basicGroup:)
Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO10bas.abstract: Some data of a basic group has changed. This update is guaranteed to come before the basic group identifier is returned to the client

Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO10sup.name: supergroup(supergroup:)
Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO10sup.abstract: Some data of a supergroup or a channel has changed. This update is guaranteed to come before the supergroup identifier is returned to the client

Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO10sec.name: secretChat(secretChat:)
Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO10sec.abstract: Some data of a secret chat has changed. This update is guaranteed to come before the secret chat identifier is returned to the client

Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO12use.name: userFullInfo(userId:userFullInfo:)
Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO12use.abstract: Some data from userFullInfo has been changed

Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO18bas.name: basicGroupFullInfo(basicGroupId:basicGroupFullInfo:)
Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO18bas.abstract: Some data from basicGroupFullInfo has been changed

Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO18sup.name: supergroupFullInfo(supergroupId:supergroupFullInfo:)
Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO18sup.abstract: Some data from supergroupFullInfo has been changed

Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO19ser.name: serviceNotification(type:content:)
Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO19ser.abstract: Service notification from the server. Upon receiving this the client must show a popup with the content of the notification

Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO19fil.name: fileGenerationStart(generationId:originalPath:destinationPath:conversion:)
Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO19fil.abstract: The file generation process needs to be started by the client

Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO4call.name: call(call:)
Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO4call.abstract: New call was created or information about a call was updated

Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO23use.name: userPrivacySettingRules(setting:rules:)
Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO23use.abstract: Some privacy setting rules have been changed

Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO18unr.name: unreadMessageCount(chatList:unreadCount:unreadUnmutedCount:)
Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO18unr.abstract: Number of unread messages in a chat list has changed. This update is sent only if the message database is used

Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO15unr.name: unreadChatCount(chatList:totalCount:unreadCount:unreadUnmutedCount:markedAsUnreadCount:markedAsUnreadUnmutedCount:)
Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO15unr.abstract: Number of unread chats, i.e. with unread messages or marked as unread, has changed. This update is sent only if the message database is used

Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO20ins.name: installedStickerSets(isMasks:stickerSetIds:)
Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO20ins.abstract: The list of installed sticker sets was updated

Enums/Update.html#/s:5TDLib6UpdateO19tre.name: trendingStickerSets(stickerSets:)
